{"type":"message","id":"45c22ef0","parentId":"9f7db481","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:09:07.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `developer` agent has only 2 bytes in its sessions.json, meaning it's never been used or something. The `senior-backend` agent has been used before.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to spawn agents via CLI (which hangs), let me just implement S1 directly as the orchestrator. I can:\n\n1. Create the backend (Python/Flask/YOLO detection)\n2. Create the frontend (React/Vite/Dashboard)\n3. Create Docker compose\n\nThis is within my capabilities as an AI assistant. The agents can be used later for review or refinement.\n\nLet me just start building S1. I'll create:\n\n\nSetting up the directory structure with backend, frontend, and Docker compose files, then implement the detection engine using Python with Flask and YOLO for processing video files.","thinkingSignature":"be2da0c5d0005b75aabc23cb53e5397e1802de258877a28c466a1bcaed98d641"},{"type":"text","text":"`openclaw agents spawn` đang block — có vẻ gateway đang bận. Tôi sẽ implement trực tiếp S1 ngay và đây, sau đó dùng agents để review.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pjaxe04i935x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pkill -f \"openclaw agents\" 2>/dev/null; echo \"cleaned\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":238,"output":274,"cacheRead":29567,"cacheWrite":596,"totalTokens":30675,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776787741739,"responseId":"0636d41ee364be1be39e89f200d8cbfb"}}
