{"type":"message","id":"54d49f8e","parentId":"8868f3b2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:31:49.304Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also, the key issue is that the `video_processor.py` converts BGR to RGB before passing to the detector, but the `app.py` `/api/detect` endpoint passes the raw BGR frame. Let me fix the `app.py` to convert BGR to RGB before processing, OR fix the detector to handle BGR (which it already should since it converts to HSV internally regardless of input color space).\n\nActually wait - the detector converts BGR→HSV internally in `_detect_helmet` and `_detect_vest`. The issue is that the raw BGR pixel values (from JPEG-compressed data) might be slightly different from the uncompressed values. This is expected behavior.\n \nI should focus on getting the demo working end-to-end with a real video file and then test the full pipeline. The Flask app crashed due to a threading signal issue with eventlet, but since the detection pipeline itself is functioning, I can either switch to a standard Flask dev server or address the eventlet problem directly.","thinkingSignature":"0931817acff4b8bb8739ca1b12709b0147cd84711f076d22380af6b477cfc544"},{"type":"text","text":"Giờ fix eventlet crash trong app.py — dùng threading thay vì eventlet:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gzcbt0y458d3_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py","edits":[{"oldText":"from flask import Flask, jsonify, request, Response\nfrom flask_socketio import SocketIO, emit\nfrom flask_cors import CORS","newText":"from flask import Flask, jsonify, request, Response\nfrom flask_socketio import SocketIO, emit, join_room, leave_room\nfrom flask_cors import CORS"},{"oldText":"app.config[\"SECRET\"] = os.getenv(\"SECRET\", \"ppe-safety-secret-key\")\nCORS(app, resources={r\"/*\": {\"origins\": \"*\"}})\nsocketio = SocketIO(\n    app,\n    cors_allowed_origins=\"*\",\n    async_mode=\"eventlet\",\n    ping_timeout=30,\n    ping_interval=10,\n)","newText":"app.config[\"SECRET\"] = os.getenv(\"SECRET\", \"ppe-safety-secret-key\")\nCORS(app, resources={r\"/*\": {\"origins\": \"*\"}})\nsocketio = SocketIO(\n    app,\n    cors_allowed_origins=\"*\",\n    async_mode=\"threading\",  # threading instead of eventlet (more stable)\n    ping_timeout=30,\n    ping_interval=10,\n)"},{"oldText":"    socketio.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=5000, debug=DEBUG)","newText":"    # Use standard Flask run (threaded) — better stability\n    app.run(host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=int(os.getenv(\"PORT\", 5000)), debug=DEBUG, threaded=True)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":645,"cacheRead":79517,"cacheWrite":2386,"totalTokens":82624,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776789097170,"responseId":"0636d96a00fa53cab4f81c7a11c42355"}}
