{"type":"message","id":"d0e83824","parentId":"754200a3","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:35:01.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue! In PyMongo 4.6+, the `Collection` object doesn't support `bool()` testing directly. The check `if not alerts_collection:` throws an error when `alerts_collection` is a real MongoDB Collection object (not `None`). \n\nI need to fix all the `if alerts_collection:` and `if not alerts_collection:` checks to use `if alerts_collection is not None:` instead.\n\nLet me fix this quickly.","thinkingSignature":"d6d308d0d82afbd38de9344669ca0b052d98dc9ba66cba19f2637db2b89fd430"},{"type":"text","text":"Rồi — bug `pymongo` mới không cho `if alerts_collection:`. Fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pcuuqdfrgtq9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"if alerts_collection\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":6075,"output":177,"cacheRead":91007,"cacheWrite":327,"totalTokens":97586,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776789293624,"responseId":"0636da2eb43e374693f77da65b7d927e"}}
