{"type":"message","id":"a9bfa043","parentId":"c5b864f7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:54:36.291Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to see the actual video feed on the dashboard - they want the video player to show what's being detected, not just statistics. The current dashboard uses a canvas to draw bounding boxes, but doesn't show the actual video frames. Let me update the dashboard to show the video feed with the annotated detections overlaid on the actual video frames.\n\nI need to:\n1. Add an endpoint to stream video frames from the backend\n2. Update the frontend to show the actual video with bounding boxes overlaid\n3. Or use the annotated frame from the backend\n\nLet me think about the best approach. The current pipeline:\n- Backend processes video frames at 2fps\n\n\n- Sends summaries via Socket.IO, but the frontend canvas just draws boxes from detection data\n\nI could serve the raw video file and overlay detections on the client side, but that's complex. A simpler solution is to have the backend return annotated frames and display those directly on the frontend, or leverage the Socket.IO connection to stream detection data alongside the video playback.\n\nThe issue is that the current setup doesn't show actual video at all—just a canvas with simulated boxes. I need to add a video element to display the source footage and overlay real-time detection boxes on top of it. The simplest path forward is adding a `/api/video_feed` endpoint that serves individual frames from the processed video, then updating the frontend to render those frames alongside the overlay visualization.\n\nFor production I'd want proper streaming with FFmpeg, but for a demo I can just add a `/api/annotated_frame` endpoint that returns the latest processed frame as a JPEG, and stream video metadata through Socket.IO to sync the bounding box overlays. The current frontend canvas already draws boxes based on detection data, so I just need to make sure the boxes stay synchronized with the video playback.\n\nBuilding the annotated frame endpoint...\n\nActually, I should reconsider—the user wants to see the actual video feed, not just synthetic graphics. The cleanest approach for a demo would be to serve the video file directly and layer the detection boxes on top via Canvas, or embed the video in an iframe and fetch the annotated frames separately. Since the backend is already processing frames, I'll add an endpoint that returns the latest annotated frame as a JPEG, then use JavaScript to overlay bounding boxes on top of the video element. This gives us a proper video player with real-time detection visualization.","thinkingSignature":"0e38f9e59fbe52dc450d465e02188032b938475b963377f2f071d13a6b3f9c80"},{"type":"text","text":"Hiểu rồi — dashboard cần hiển thị **video thực** chứ không phải canvas giả. Tôi fix ngay:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_78yuybmuo7l4_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py","offset":170,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":577,"cacheRead":101874,"cacheWrite":994,"totalTokens":103445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776790460193,"responseId":"0636debe7b8b976b7fd92f010e959681"}}
{"type":"message","id":"05b15da7","parentId":"a9bfa043","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:54:36.354Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_78yuybmuo7l4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n        return jsonify(response)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        return jsonify({\"error\": str(e)}), 500\n\n\n@app.route(\"/api/summary\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef get_summary():\n    \"\"\"Get latest detection summary from running processor.\"\"\"\n    if not processor:\n        return jsonify({\"error\": \"Processor not initialized\"}), 503\n\n    results = processor.get_latest_results()\n    return jsonify({\n        **results,\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n    })\n\n\n@app.route(\"/api/alerts\", methods=[\"GET\"])\ndef get_alerts():\n    \"\"\"Get recent alerts from MongoDB.\"\"\"\n    if alerts_collection is None:\n        return jsonify([])\n\n    limit = int(request.args.get(\"limit\", 50))\n    cursor = alerts_collection.find(\n        {},\n        {\"_id\": 0}\n\n[116 more lines in file. Use offset=200 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776790476325}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0ce249d","parentId":"05b15da7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:54:43.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add an endpoint that serves the latest annotated frame. Let me add a `/api/frame` endpoint that returns the latest processed frame as a JPEG. I also need to modify the VideoProcessor to store the latest annotated frame.\n\nActually, the VideoProcessor already stores the last results in `self._last_results` and `self._last_summary`. I need to also store the last annotated frame. Let me:\n\n1. Add a `/api/frame` endpoint that returns the latest annotated frame\n2. Update the VideoProcessor to store the latest annotated frame3. Update the frontend to show video + overlayLet me update the video_processor.py to store the latest annotated frame, and add the endpoint to app.py.","thinkingSignature":"e3ce18d7ab907286c34ea9d7ef2a20620da8988d53037d552d08050a1a936dba"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cn8q0svb3krk_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","offset":1,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":204,"output":210,"cacheRead":103443,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103857,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776790476376,"responseId":"0636decd94a0c2bf7e943fa611a7e80d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"11cc5398","parentId":"d0ce249d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T16:54:43.579Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cn8q0svb3krk_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nVideo Processor — Reads video file frame by frame and emits detections.\nCan also use webcam for live input.\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport time\nimport threading\nfrom collections import deque\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\n\nclass VideoProcessor:\n    \"\"\"\n    Processes video files (or webcam) and yields detection results per frame.\n    Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n        self.video_path = video_path\n        self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n        self.fps_target = fps_target  # Process every Nth frame for performance\n        self.detector = PPEDetector()\n        self._running = False\n        self._thread = None\n        self._frame_count = 0\n        self._last_results = []\n        self._last_summary = {}\n        self._lock = threading.Lock()\n        # Callbacks\n        self.on_detection = None  # Called with (frame_rgb, detections, summary)\n        self.on_violation = None   # Called when violation detected\n\n    def start(self, on_detection=None, on_violation=None):\n        \"\"\"Start processing in a background thread.\"\"\"\n        self.on_detection = on_detection\n        self.on_violation = on_violation\n        self._running = True\n        self._thread = threading.Thread(target=self._process_loop, daemon=True)\n        self._thread.start()\n\n[131 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776790483552}}
