{"type":"message","id":"db3331ae","parentId":"eb61d006","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:05:30.837Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is `EPIPE` - a socket write error to the Flask backend. This happens because Flask's dev server doesn't support Range requests that video players need. When the video player makes a Range request (to seek), Flask returns an error or partial response.\n\nThis is the classic problem: Flask's development server can't handle Range requests that HTML5 video players use for seeking/buffering. I need to either:\n1. Serve the video directly through a proper web server (nginx)\n2. Or use a different approach - serve video as a static file from Vite's public directory\n\nThe simplest fix: serve the video from the frontend's public directory. Since Vite serves static files from `/public`, I can copy the video there and it will be served directly by Vite.\n\n\nI'll copy the video to the frontend's public directory so Vite can serve it directly, which bypasses Flask's limitations entirely.","thinkingSignature":"547717e30624a9b8e0c4fc75dc97fd2c473d6f95fe7334f872c3e68135075f6d"},{"type":"text","text":"Flask dev server không hỗ trợ Range requests cho video. Cách nhanh nhất: serve video trực tiếp từ Vite (frontend):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ubuhxjgzq5p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video\ncp /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4 \\\n  /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/demo.mp4\necho \"Copied! Size: $(du -sh /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/demo.mp4 | cut -f1)\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":362,"output":367,"cacheRead":123163,"cacheWrite":286,"totalTokens":124178,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0