{"type":"message","id":"364dc75f","parentId":"5586acc2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:18:36.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The video is serving correctly - Flask is listening on all interfaces (0.0.0.0:5000) and the video data is being served correctly. The issue might be:1. The Flask dev server is running but the browser might be blocking it due to CORS or mixed content issues (http vs https)\n2. The browser might be blocking cross-origin video loads\n\nWait - the issue might be that the browser sees this as a cross-origin resource. Even though `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` is present, the browser might still block it because of other reasons.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the browser says \"Không tải được video\" and shows the URL `http://103.253.21.139:5000/video/demo.mp4`. The video is being served with CORS headers.\n \nSo the problem might be something else entirely - maybe the onError handler is being triggered for a different reason than CORS, or the video element just isn't loading the source properly.\n\nLet me try serving the video from a static file server instead of Flask, or even simpler - just embed the video data directly as a blob URL or use a data URL if it's small enough. But wait, I'm realizing the real issue might be that the frontend is loading from HTTPS while the video is coming from HTTP - that's mixed content blocking. Though this should still work in most browsers with a warning. The `<video>` tag should handle CORS fine even with wildcard headers, so something else is going on here.\n\nLet me think about what's actually happening. The frontend and video are both served over HTTP on the same port, so there shouldn't be mixed content issues. But the browser is saying it can't load the video. Maybe Flask-SocketIO is interfering with how Flask handles static file serving, or there's an error in the serve_video route itself. I should add some debug logging to the Flask route to see what's actually happening.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach entirely - serving the video through nginx instead of Flask, since nginx handles static file serving much more reliably than the development server.","thinkingSignature":"5e27bfe668191d1a25f8cfc1ce3ddd05be3b935f87752950386c062dd441de63"},{"type":"text","text":"Video chạy được qua curl nhưng browser vẫn lỗi. Có thể Flask dev server không serve video đúng cách. Thử serve qua **nginx** thay vì Flask:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6khqfokk1wt2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which nginx && nginx -v 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1143,"output":520,"cacheRead":148190,"cacheWrite":302,"totalTokens":150155,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776791903906,"responseId":"0636e461dfe7776ca1814923ee771322"}}
