{"type":"message","id":"0337fbcc","parentId":"b9a84d26","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:21:07.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is seeing the same error. The issue is clear now - Vite dev server isn't starting properly and Flask is intercepting port 3003. The vite process seems to be crashing or not starting correctly.\n\nLet me take a completely different approach. Instead of fighting with video serving:\n\n1. Kill everything\n2. Start Vite properly on 3003\n3. Make sure Flask is on 5000 and NOT on 3003\n4. Serve the video from a simple Python HTTP server\n\nLet me check what's actually running on port 3003.","thinkingSignature":"1fe17d268cbffd84f33272a02714163f21a32b3ae0493580587ea6a47b75b50c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jzavkr5sukvx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep -E \"3003|5000\"\necho \"===\"\nps aux | grep -E \"vite|python3 app\" | grep -v grep","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":188,"cacheRead":6760,"cacheWrite":26735,"totalTokens":33683,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792060235,"responseId":"0636e4fd54d370ef3c141f5cac108f8f"}}
