{"type":"message","id":"70e94f89","parentId":"3c14d7da","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:21:13.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so both ports are running. Flask is on 5000, Vite on 3003. The issue is that:\n\n1. The backend (`app.py`) has a route for `/video/...` that intercepts requests\n2. Even though Vite is on 3003, when we request `/video/demo.mp4` through Vite's proxy, Flask on 5000 intercepts it and serves it with Werkzeug\n3. OR the video URL in the code still points to `http://103.253.21.139:5000/video/demo.mp4`\n\nWait - the user said the error shows `http://103.253.21.139:5000/video/demo.mp4`. That means the current code still has that URL. But I changed it to `/video/demo.mp4`. Let me check the current state of the file.","thinkingSignature":"f5e070279ed51c6f2984b321ace5123407e56d34ce2c1e62529ede5a7eb69c9b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2dwnyrmnwpy0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"VIDEO_URL\\|/video/\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/App.jsx | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":245,"cacheRead":33930,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34175,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792067713,"responseId":"0636e505e8b25e7a1c8b6ea18edd012d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f3efc05","parentId":"70e94f89","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:21:14.102Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2dwnyrmnwpy0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// Video: served by Vite dev server from public/video/\nconst VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n          src={VIDEO_URL}\n              <div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: '#888' }}>Kiểm tra đường dẫn: {VIDEO_URL}</div>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":18,"aggregated":"// Video: served by Vite dev server from public/video/\nconst VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n          src={VIDEO_URL}\n              <div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: '#888' }}>Kiểm tra đường dẫn: {VIDEO_URL}</div>","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792074096}}
{"type":"message","id":"2553dfc9","parentId":"6f3efc05","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:21:19.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the VIDEO_URL is `/video/demo.mp4`. So the video should be served from Vite's public folder. But the user is still seeing the Flask URL in the error. This means the frontend hasn't been rebuilt with the latest changes.\n\nLet me check when the last build was done and what the current built file contains.","thinkingSignature":"69e88c22427b62f789adec25b31b527362e375e835b6e4842a1d456c48a5c50b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i4ws6vvcax9l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if built file has the old URL\ngrep -r \"5000/video\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/dist/ 2>/dev/null | head -3\necho \"---\"\n# The error shows Flask URL → dev server might be serving old built files\n# Let's check if Vite is in dev mode (serves src directly) or prod mode (serves dist)\ngrep \"scripts\\|build\\|dev\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/package.json | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":112,"output":224,"cacheRead":33458,"cacheWrite":685,"totalTokens":34479,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792074107,"responseId":"0636e50b6171ae4c6a12a1bfcbbc8c5f"}}
