{"type":"message","id":"8e7357a6","parentId":"f30ca1bb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:05.471Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the built file has `/video/demo.mp4`. The Vite dev server should serve from the dist folder (since it's the built version). Let me restart the frontend.\n\nWait - `npm run dev` serves from `src/`, not from `dist/`. The `dist/` folder is only used for production builds (`npm run build`). For development, `npm run dev` uses Vite's dev server which serves directly from `src/`.\n\nBut in production, you'd serve `dist/` with a static file server. Since the user is accessing port 3003, they're using the dev server.\n\nLet me check - the frontend is running `npm run dev` which serves from `src/`. \n\nSo I need to verify whether the dev server is actually running and serving the updated source code.","thinkingSignature":"913d61c74f9dc463c7f5c9446d5fe5bd183b5734b5e80ff336abb4e4bb50e324"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zbni6g7wvju2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"vite.*3003\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2, $10}'\necho \"---\"\ngrep \"VIDEO_URL\\|5000\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/App.jsx | head -3","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":114,"output":260,"cacheRead":48608,"cacheWrite":575,"totalTokens":49557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792120081,"responseId":"0636e539ffcc2722cd5144ea27e89150"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3c86d0d","parentId":"8e7357a6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:05.618Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zbni6g7wvju2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"606858 0:00\n606859 0:05\n---\nconst VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n          src={VIDEO_URL}\n              <div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: '#888' }}>Kiểm tra đường dẫn: {VIDEO_URL}</div>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":91,"aggregated":"606858 0:00\n606859 0:05\n---\nconst VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n          src={VIDEO_URL}\n              <div style={{ fontSize: 12, color: '#888' }}>Kiểm tra đường dẫn: {VIDEO_URL}</div>","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792125611}}
{"type":"message","id":"04007530","parentId":"d3c86d0d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:16.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The source file has `VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'`. The Vite dev server is running (pids 606858, 606859). Vite's dev server serves directly from `src/`, so it should use the updated source. Let me check if the Vite dev server picked up the changes - it uses HMR (Hot Module Replacement) so it should auto-reload.\n\nBut the user is still seeing the old URL. This is because:\n1. The browser cached the old JS\n2. Even with HMR, the browser might need a refresh\n\nLet me check if the Vite dev server is actually working correctly. The issue might be that Vite serves from `src/` with HMR, but the browser's JS cache is stale.\n\n\nThe timestamps show the Vite process has been running for a while (the 0:05 indicates 5 minutes of CPU time, but that's likely accumulated over the session), and the source file was updated at 17:19, so Vite should have automatically reloaded with HMR. The real problem is probably that the browser itself is caching the old JavaScript, not that the dev server hasn't updated. The issue is that Vite's dev server is intercepting the `/video` requests and returning a 404, even though I removed the proxy configuration. The Flask backend has a `/media/` route instead now, but the browser is still trying to fetch `/video/demo.mp4` through Vite, which doesn't have that route configured anymore. So there's a mismatch between what the frontend is requesting and what the backend is actually serving.\n\nWait, I think I've been misunderstanding the architecture. The Flask backend is running on port 5000 and Vite is on port 3003, so when the browser requests `/video/demo.mp4`, it goes to Vite first. Vite should be checking its `public/video/` directory, but something's not matching up there.\n\nLet me verify the file actually exists in that location and check what the Vite dev server logs are showing.","thinkingSignature":"0cb095665705d9678116fd3422385ab14b9113c22ca30c94ab9229a3e267eddb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_neo07s3uigfg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/\necho \"---\"\ncurl -sI http://localhost:3003/video/demo.mp4 | head -6\necho \"---\"\n# Kill old vite and restart clean\nkill $(ps aux | grep \"vite.*3003\" | grep -v grep | awk '{print $2}') 2>/dev/null\nsleep 3\ncd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend && \\\nnohup npm run dev -- --host > /tmp/s1-frontend.log 2>&1 &\necho \"Restarted PID: $!\"\nsleep 8\ncurl -sI http://localhost:3003/video/demo.mp4 | head -6","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":114,"output":619,"cacheRead":49043,"cacheWrite":482,"totalTokens":50258,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792125622,"responseId":"0636e53e02ce6dddee1c3bb46edbc034"}}
