{"type":"message","id":"af3e2bac","parentId":"d5cdda76","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:35.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even after restarting Vite, port 3003 still returns 404 for `/video/demo.mp4`. And the server header says `Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12` - which means Flask is somehow on port 3003 too!\n\nWait - this is strange. The Flask backend should only be on port 5000. But the response from port 3003 shows `Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12` as the server. This means Flask IS running on port 3003 somehow.\n\nOR... could there be another Flask process? Let me check.","thinkingSignature":"e7a16a24c25751ffa53781e6a3d7ace90e38322f943ae9051bbdf01415fd4835"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2pbr78ehgjin_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep -E \"3003|5000\"\necho \"---\"\nps aux | grep python | grep -v grep","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":263,"output":196,"cacheRead":49602,"cacheWrite":723,"totalTokens":50784,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792150053,"responseId":"0636e557d7b061f8210e5682b308140d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"58bf8746","parentId":"af3e2bac","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:35.607Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2pbr78ehgjin_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LISTEN 0      128          0.0.0.0:5000       0.0.0.0:*    users:((\"python3\",pid=606766,fd=7))         \nLISTEN 0      511                *:3003             *:*    users:((\"node\",pid=607695,fd=24))           \n---\nroot         611  0.0  0.1  33076  9592 ?        Ss   Apr13   0:00 /usr/bin/python3 /usr/bin/networkd-dispatcher --run-startup-triggers\nroot         778  0.0  0.1 110156 11388 ?        Ssl  Apr13   0:00 /usr/bin/python3 /usr/share/unattended-upgrades/unattended-upgrade-shutdown --wait-for-signal\nroot      606766 18.4  1.6 1611976 131684 ?      Sl   17:19   0:29 python3 app.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":65,"aggregated":"LISTEN 0      128          0.0.0.0:5000       0.0.0.0:*    users:((\"python3\",pid=606766,fd=7))         \nLISTEN 0      511                *:3003             *:*    users:((\"node\",pid=607695,fd=24))           \n---\nroot         611  0.0  0.1  33076  9592 ?        Ss   Apr13   0:00 /usr/bin/python3 /usr/bin/networkd-dispatcher --run-startup-triggers\nroot         778  0.0  0.1 110156 11388 ?        Ssl  Apr13   0:00 /usr/bin/python3 /usr/share/unattended-upgrades/unattended-upgrade-shutdown --wait-for-signal\nroot      606766 18.4  1.6 1611976 131684 ?      Sl   17:19   0:29 python3 app.py","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792155602}}
{"type":"message","id":"200e77cb","parentId":"58bf8746","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:44.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n- Port 5000: Flask (python3 app.py, pid 606766)\n- Port 3003: Node/Vite (pid 607695)\n\nBut curl to port 3003 returns `Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12`? That doesn't make sense. Unless the old Flask process is still somehow bound to port 3003... but no, only one process can bind to a port.\n\nWait, maybe Vite is proxying `/video` requests to Flask on port 5000, and the curl is going through Vite's proxy to Flask. \n\nAh, I see it now—Vite's proxy is forwarding `/video` requests to `http://localhost:5000`, and Flask's route handler for that path is returning the 404. The headers confirm it's reaching Flask through the proxy. But I removed the `/video` proxy config earlier, so something's still forwarding those requests.\n\nLooking back at my edits, I only modified the `/video` proxy block but kept the `/socket.io` proxy intact. The old `/video` proxy config I thought I'd removed is still there in the current vite.config.js, which means the proxy hasn't actually been disabled yet.\n\nThe real problem is that even with the proxy removed, when a browser requests `/video/demo.mp4` from Vite on port 3003, Vite doesn't know how to serve it from the public directory—it's hitting the proxy config instead. But since I just killed and restarted Vite, the current state should reflect my last edit where I removed the proxy block entirely. Let me verify what's actually in the vite.config.js right now.","thinkingSignature":"3f7f0a36670e242a9e741a7bb6de85fa6d9358df2b3daadeec5c24623198f02f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ev4duoncxj43_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"salty-haven","limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":274,"output":393,"cacheRead":50268,"cacheWrite":484,"totalTokens":51419,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792155612,"responseId":"0636e55c53ab79e4466d0e921ae316f4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0e57002","parentId":"200e77cb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:44.601Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ev4duoncxj43_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"total 696\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root   4096 Apr 21 17:05 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root   4096 Apr 21 17:05 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 703785 Apr 21 17:05 demo.mp4\n---\nHTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\nVary: Origin\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:22:16 GMT\ncontent-type: text/html; charset=utf-8\ncontent-length: 207\n---\nRestarted PID: 607682\nHTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\nVary: Origin\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:22:27 GMT\ncontent-type: text/html; charset=utf-8\ncontent-length: 207"}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"salty-haven","total":19,"totalLines":19,"totalChars":533,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"ls /root/.openclaw/worksp...frontend/public/video/"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792164596}}
{"type":"message","id":"a80be6bb","parentId":"f0e57002","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:55.311Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Vite dev server is returning 404 with Werkzeug server header. That's strange - Vite shouldn't return Werkzeug headers. Unless... \n\nOh! I think I understand now. Looking at the curl output:\n```\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\n```\n\nThis says the response comes from Werkzeug. But Vite is a Node.js server. This means that either:\n1. The Flask backend is ALSO running on port 3003 somehow\n2. OR Vite is proxying to Flask which is on 5000, and the proxy adds Flask's headers\n\nWait - looking at the curl response headers again:\n\n\n```\nVary: Origin\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\n```\n\n`Vary: Origin` and `Werkzeug` headers together strongly suggest this IS coming from Flask. But Flask is on port 5000, not 3003. Unless there's a port conflict or something else is going on.\n\nActually, I think the old Vite process is still running even though I tried to kill it. The PIDs I found might not be the right ones to terminate, so the new Vite process couldn't bind to port 3003 and either fell back to Flask or something else is intercepting the request. Vite process. Let me check.\n\nActually wait - looking at the `ss` output:\n```\nLISTEN 0      511                *:3003             *:*    users:((\"node\",pid=607695,fd=24))\n```\n\nPort 3003 is bound by a node process (pid 607695). But curl shows `Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12`. This is impossible unless...\n\nActually, I think what's happening is:\n1. Browser makes request to `http://103.253.21.139:3003/video/demo.mp4`\n2. Something (maybe iptables or a reverse proxy) is redirecting port 3003 traffic to port 5000\n3. Flask on 5000 handles the request, returns 404 because `/video/...` was renamed to `/media/...`\n\nThat doesn't make sense either. Let me try a different approach entirely - I'll set up a simple Python HTTP server on a different port just to serve the video files, completely bypassing both Flask and Vite for this static content.","thinkingSignature":"8e423c924cf95b216e61b8b6bddefde6c2689bb113a6442331314b9a9bccfd4a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_urezj751pr5c_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Test: what's actually on port 3003?\ncurl -s http://localhost:3003/ | head -20\necho \"---\"\n# Check if Flask is also somehow on 3003\nss -tlnp | grep 3003","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":263,"output":582,"cacheRead":50551,"cacheWrite":836,"totalTokens":52232,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792164610,"responseId":"0636e5659353cfa326956c75a98f2cef"}}
