{"type":"message","id":"ad77f626","parentId":"85c6f788","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:59.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so port 3003 IS serving Vite's dev server (it returns the HTML with `/@react-refresh` and `/@vite/client`). So Vite is on 3003. But why does `/video/demo.mp4` return Werkzeug headers?\n\nLet me check the video URL directly from the Vite server:","thinkingSignature":"6c269ead0afbbd3d83d98cf05847d239c764bcaa9a9fe1cb16d9b52ba2b5ca84"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lnvtki25n2ou_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sv http://localhost:3003/video/demo.mp4 2>&1 | grep -E \"HTTP|server|Location|trying\" | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":244,"output":136,"cacheRead":50989,"cacheWrite":1211,"totalTokens":52580,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792175496,"responseId":"0636e57038c774e7f2ca6c405675ab4f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2686671","parentId":"ad77f626","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:22:59.920Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lnvtki25n2ou_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"> GET /video/demo.mp4 HTTP/1.1\r\n< HTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\r\n< server: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\n<p>The requested URL was not found on the server. If you entered the URL manually please check your spelling and try again.</p>"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":45,"aggregated":"> GET /video/demo.mp4 HTTP/1.1\r\n< HTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\r\n< server: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\n<p>The requested URL was not found on the server. If you entered the URL manually please check your spelling and try again.</p>","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792179914}}
{"type":"message","id":"d7e3d3f8","parentId":"d2686671","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:06.868Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very strange. Port 3003 is clearly Vite (it serves the HTML correctly), but `/video/demo.mp4` returns a Werkzeug 404. This means Flask must also be somehow accessible on port 3003.\n\nOH WAIT! I think I understand now. When I use `curl http://localhost:3003`, the Host header is `localhost:3003`. But when Vite's proxy forwards to Flask, the Host header becomes `localhost:5000`. BUT... there's only one Flask process on port 5000.\n\nUnless... the Flask app has some route that intercepts all requests? No, that doesn't make sense.\n \nActually, I'm realizing the Werkzeug server header is a red herring—Vite's proxy might be adding that when forwarding requests to Flask, or there's another Flask instance running on port 3003 that I'm missing. Let me check if there's a second process I haven't spotted yet.","thinkingSignature":"cc8463d43d50306d14440d49935af40073d41e5ca8132819758c3c9a6910cb42"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mfnrn0yk0vlj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep -E \"3003|5000|5001\"\necho \"---\"\n# Maybe Flask is proxying through something\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:3003/video/demo.mp4 2>&1 | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check what's on the VPS external IP\ncurl -s --connect-to \"103.253.21.139:3003:127.0.0.1:3003\" http://103.253.21.139/video/demo.mp4 2>&1 | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":116,"output":349,"cacheRead":51613,"cacheWrite":935,"totalTokens":53013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792179924,"responseId":"0636e5743caea897179a4ff6fee3cd97"}}
