{"type":"message","id":"22be455c","parentId":"7133ecd4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:11.062Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3003/video/demo.mp4` returns an HTML page with `404 Not Found` but NO `server: Werkzeug` header. That's interesting. Let me check:","thinkingSignature":"c50ff84fdc8ea7751b1720e0868ffe9c533f1da8ade088e4ee081c86e35f3531"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z0myg8a8gzk2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sI http://127.0.0.1:3003/video/demo.mp4 | head -10\necho \"---\"\ncurl -sI http://127.0.0.1:3003/ | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":181,"output":135,"cacheRead":52407,"cacheWrite":574,"totalTokens":53297,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792186983,"responseId":"0636e57bad0d8b1e1253f524f9dc8e74"}}
{"type":"message","id":"00e776b8","parentId":"22be455c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:11.152Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z0myg8a8gzk2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\r\nVary: Origin\r\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:23:11 GMT\r\ncontent-type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\ncontent-length: 207\r\naccess-control-allow-origin: *\r\nconnection: close\r\n\r\n---\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nVary: Origin\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\nCache-Control: no-cache\r\nEtag: W/\"23c-0IQwq4s1GBMaYEiBEQjFNzbiWOE\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":45,"aggregated":"HTTP/1.1 404 NOT FOUND\r\nVary: Origin\r\nserver: Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\r\ndate: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:23:11 GMT\r\ncontent-type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\ncontent-length: 207\r\naccess-control-allow-origin: *\r\nconnection: close\r\n\r\n---\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nVary: Origin\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\nCache-Control: no-cache\r\nEtag: W/\"23c-0IQwq4s1GBMaYEiBEQjFNzbiWOE\"","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792191147}}
{"type":"message","id":"7091a197","parentId":"00e776b8","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:20.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So:\n- `http://127.0.0.1:3003/` → 200, no Werkzeug header (this is Vite)\n- `http://127.0.0.1:3003/video/demo.mp4` → 404, WITH `server: Werkzeug` header\n\nThis is bizarre. Vite on port 3003 serves the root but somehow `/video/...` returns a Werkzeug response. But the port is the same...\n\nWait - could Vite's proxy be forwarding `/video` to Flask on 5000, but Flask is ALSO somehow accessible on port 3003?\n \nOr maybe Flask is binding to 0.0.0.0:3003 instead of 5000? I don't see it in the socket list though. What if Flask is running as a background thread within the Vite process itself? I did restart Vite and killed old processes, so there shouldn't be lingering instances.\n\nLooking at the Flask startup log, it was started with `MONGO_URI` and `DEBUG` environment variables, which points to the VPS. But the Flask PID is 606766, and it should be listening on 0.0.0.0:5000. Maybe Flask is somehow accessible through a reverse proxy or iptables rule mapping 3003 to 5000? Though that seems unlikely. The 404 response is interesting too — Flask changed the route from `/video/<path:filename>` to `/media/<path:filename>`, so if a request somehow reaches Flask on 5000, it would 404 for `/video`. But the port mismatch is the real puzzle here.\n\nWhat if Flask is also bound to port 3003 somehow? Let me check the actual listening sockets more carefully to see what's really running on that port.","thinkingSignature":"ce5eb0190be77c05f12b140fc88e34e9fc6dccee591000c7771c9790132d6fca"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_82a1liaym9wj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep 3003\necho \"---\"\n# Check if there are any nginx or other proxies\nps aux | grep -E \"nginx|apache|proxy\" | grep -v grep\necho \"---\"\n# Try lsof on port 3003\nlsof -i :3003 2>/dev/null | head -5","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":181,"output":478,"cacheRead":52627,"cacheWrite":638,"totalTokens":53924,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792191156,"responseId":"0636e5809d83ac87e25c7ebcfe6032fb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7515e172","parentId":"7091a197","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:27.071Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_82a1liaym9wj_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LISTEN 0      511                *:3003             *:*    users:((\"node\",pid=607695,fd=24))           \n---\nroot      528343  0.0  0.0 1671208 1104 ?        Sl   Apr20   0:01 /usr/bin/docker-proxy -proto tcp -host-ip 0.0.0.0 -host-port 27017 -container-ip 172.17.0.2 -container-port 27017 -use-listen-fd\nroot      528350  0.0  0.0 1671208 2280 ?        Sl   Apr20   0:14 /usr/bin/docker-proxy -proto tcp -host-ip :: -host-port 27017 -container-ip 172.17.0.2 -container-port 27017 -use-listen-fd\n---\nCOMMAND    PID USER   FD   TYPE  DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME\nnode    607695 root   24u  IPv6 8033230      0t0  TCP *:3003 (LISTEN)\nnode    607695 root   27u  IPv6 8033257      0t0  TCP atu-ahv-ai006:3003->42.119.92.253:23394 (ESTABLISHED)\n\nCommand timed out after 5 seconds. If this command is expected to take longer, re-run with a higher timeout (e.g., exec timeout=300). If it should keep running, start it with exec background=true or yieldMs so OpenClaw can register a pollable process session. Do not rely on shell backgrounding with a trailing &."}],"details":{"status":"failed","exitCode":null,"durationMs":6858,"aggregated":"LISTEN 0      511                *:3003             *:*    users:((\"node\",pid=607695,fd=24))           \n---\nroot      528343  0.0  0.0 1671208 1104 ?        Sl   Apr20   0:01 /usr/bin/docker-proxy -proto tcp -host-ip 0.0.0.0 -host-port 27017 -container-ip 172.17.0.2 -container-port 27017 -use-listen-fd\nroot      528350  0.0  0.0 1671208 2280 ?        Sl   Apr20   0:14 /usr/bin/docker-proxy -proto tcp -host-ip :: -host-port 27017 -container-ip 172.17.0.2 -container-port 27017 -use-listen-fd\n---\nCOMMAND    PID USER   FD   TYPE  DEVICE SIZE/OFF NODE NAME\nnode    607695 root   24u  IPv6 8033230      0t0  TCP *:3003 (LISTEN)\