{"type":"message","id":"3135e549","parentId":"7515e172","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:33.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so port 3003 is definitely only node (Vite). There's a TCP connection from port 3003 to `42.119.92.253:23394` which is likely the browser (user's IP from Vietnam). But the `/video/demo.mp4` request returns a Werkzeug response. \n\nWait - could the Vite proxy be forwarding `/video` requests to Flask on port 5000? Let me check if Vite's proxy config still has the `/video` proxy entry.\n\nActually, looking at the vite.config.js more carefully:\n```js\nserver: {\n  port: 3003,\n  proxy: {\n    '/api': {\n      target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n      changeOrigin: true,\n    },\n    '/socket.io': {\n      target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n      ws: true,\n    },\n  },\n},\n```\n\nNo `/video` proxy. But wait - maybe there was a proxy config that I changed earlier? Let me verify what the current vite.config.js actually contains.","thinkingSignature":"0ca106aa8774398842e9a5faf3523364f4b342af06502cb8e9e03e6e6dffbadc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bj1jq8e17540_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":407,"output":261,"cacheRead":53125,"cacheWrite":767,"totalTokens":54560,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792207078,"responseId":"0636e5909d1338162fddf1482ce320c0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c48d6696","parentId":"3135e549","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:33.075Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bj1jq8e17540_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [react()],\n  server: {\n    port: 3003,\n    proxy: {\n      '/api': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        changeOrigin: true,\n      },\n      '/socket.io': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        ws: true,\n      },\n      '/video': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        changeOrigin: true,\n      },\n    },\n  },\n})\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792213070}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f6483d1","parentId":"c48d6696","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:23:41.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There IS still a `/video` proxy in the vite.config.js! When I tried to remove it, it was still there. So the `/video` proxy forwards to Flask on port 5000. And Flask changed `/video` to `/media`, so Flask returns 404.\n\nNow I need to:1. Remove the `/video` proxy from vite.config.js\n2. Serve the video from a different source\n\nOR:3. Keep the proxy but serve the video from Flask using the new `/media` URL\n\nActually, let me take a completely different approach. The simplest solution is to serve the video from a simple Python HTTP server that's separate from Flask. Let me:\n\n\n1. Remove the `/video` proxy from vite.config.js\n2. Start a simple Python HTTP server on a different port (like 8080) to serve static files\n3. Point the frontend to that server for video files\n\nOr I could just use Vite's public folder since the file is already there—Vite should serve static files from `public/` directly without needing a proxy. Let me check if removing the proxy actually fixes this.","thinkingSignature":"ecd24c68705dffe820cd9e23fa30ea4a7161efd5647f7a3ce41ae46ab6841454"},{"type":"text","text":"Thì ra `/video` proxy vẫn còn trong vite.config! Xóa nó đi để Vite serve trực tiếp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5mqmaav09cpm_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js","edits":[{"oldText":"      '/socket.io': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        ws: true,\n      },\n      '/video': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        changeOrigin: true,\n      },","newText":"      '/socket.io': {\n        target: 'http://localhost:5000',\n        ws: true,\n      },"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":169,"output":418,"cacheRead":53409,"cacheWrite":1119,"totalTokens":55115,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792213079,"responseId":"0636e596bef4e97ee566aebdfe0d3d98"}}
