{"type":"message","id":"2103e0b3","parentId":"cd645df7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:25:52.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"ffmpeg-python just wraps the system ffmpeg binary, but ffmpeg isn't installed. Let me try a different approach - use Python to manually rearrange the MP4 atoms. This is actually doable - I can parse the MP4 structure and move the moov atom to the beginning.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The issue is that the MP4 file has moov at the end. I can write a Python script to:1. Read the MP4 file\n2. Parse all top-level atoms (boxes)\n3. Reorder them so moov comes first, followed by ftyp, then mdat4. Write the outputThis is a well-known MP4 manipulation task. \n\nNow I'll write a script to handle the atom reordering.","thinkingSignature":"bbd7bc5229408c5c000819d3be6c6e0d28001577baca2c47fb45068b6e9e4c17"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cvf3ah60ar34_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Use Python struct to rearrange MP4 atoms - move moov to front\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport struct, os\n\nsrc = '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/demo.mp4'\ndst = '/tmp/demo_fixed.mp4'\n\nwith open(src, 'rb') as f:\n    data = f.read()\n\n# Parse top-level MP4 atoms\ndef parse_atom(data, offset=0):\n    atoms = []\n    while offset < len(data):\n        if offset + 8 > len(data):\n            break\n        size = struct.unpack('>I', data[offset:offset+4])[0]\n        name = data[offset+4:offset+8].decode('ascii', errors='replace')\n        if size == 0:\n            size = len(data) - offset\n        if size < 8:\n            break\n        atoms.append((name, offset, size))\n        offset += size\n    return atoms\n\natoms = parse_atom(data)\nprint(\"Atoms found:\", [(a[0], a[2]) for a in atoms])\n\n# Reorder: moov first, then ftyp, then mdat, then rest\ndef reorder_atoms(atoms):\n    moov = next((a for a in atoms if a[0] == 'moov'), None)\n    ftyp = next((a for a in atoms if a[0] == 'ftyp'), None)\n    mdat = next((a for a in atoms if a[0] == 'mdat'), None)\n    others = [a for a in atoms if a[0] not in ('moov', 'ftyp', 'mdat')]\n    order = []\n    if moov: order.append(moov)\n    if ftyp: order.append(ftyp)\n    if mdat: order.append(mdat)\n    order.extend(others)\n    return order\n\nordered = reorder_atoms(atoms)\nprint(\"New order:\", [a[0] for a in ordered])\n\n# Write reordered file\nwith open(dst, 'wb') as f:\n    for name, offset, size in ordered:\n        f.write(data[offset:offset+size])\n\n# Verify\nwith open(dst, 'rb') as f:\n    new_data = f.read()\n\nnew_atoms = parse_atom(new_data)\nprint(\"New file atoms:\", [(a[0], a[2]) for a in new_atoms])\nprint(f\"Original: {len(data)} bytes, Fixed: {len(new_data)} bytes\")\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":237,"output":720,"cacheRead":53793,"cacheWrite":488,"totalTokens":55238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792340395,"responseId":"0636e616f4d61f398d951826a37553ff"}}
