{"type":"message","id":"0a3fbf98","parentId":"4ac1f02d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:26:20.674Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user keeps seeing the old URL in the error message - `/video/demo.mp4` instead of the full URL. This is because the built JS file still has the old URL. Let me check the current state of things.\n\nWait - actually, the current App.jsx has `const VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'` which is correct (served by Vite). The error message shows `/video/demo.mp4` which is the right path. But the user still can't load video.\n\nLet me check if the browser is loading from the old built dist or from the dev server. Since the user is using `npm run dev`, the source files should be served directly by Vite's dev server, not the built dist.\n \nI'm realizing the issue might be that the built dist file has stale code even though the dev server should be serving the updated source directly. The user could be hitting the old production build instead of the dev server. Let me verify the current VIDEO_URL configuration in the source.","thinkingSignature":"fffd8648b0b0fdd374611c99508e7bd333d7a7cf83438f01cc38bdefac7442fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rlj9m0tv1b5y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep \"VIDEO_URL\\|video\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/src/App.jsx | grep -v \"//\\|import\" | head -5\necho \"---\"\n# Check if dev server is actually serving updated source\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:3003/src/App.jsx\" 2>/dev/null | grep \"VIDEO_URL\" | head -3","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":325,"cacheRead":54752,"cacheWrite":316,"totalTokens":55393,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792371953,"responseId":"0636e6359d4f96c1466ad059a4932491"}}
{"type":"message","id":"61bc30ff","parentId":"0a3fbf98","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:26:20.749Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rlj9m0tv1b5y_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n  const [videoReady, setVideoReady] = useState(false)\n  const [videoError, setVideoError] = useState(null)\n      {/* ── TOP: Plain video (observation only) ── */}\n        <video\n---\nconst VIDEO_URL = \"/video/demo.mp4\";\n          src: VIDEO_URL,\n          VIDEO_URL"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"const VIDEO_URL = '/video/demo.mp4'\n  const [videoReady, setVideoReady] = useState(false)\n  const [videoError, setVideoError] = useState(null)\n      {/* ── TOP: Plain video (observation only) ── */}\n        <video\n---\nconst VIDEO_URL = \"/video/demo.mp4\";\n          src: VIDEO_URL,\n          VIDEO_URL","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792380743}}
{"type":"message","id":"07fbe2b6","parentId":"61bc30ff","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:26:30.592Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - the dev server is serving the updated source with `const VIDEO_URL = \"/video/demo.mp4\"`. The URL is correct.\n\nThe issue is probably that the video still won't play in the browser even with moov first. This could be because:1. The video codec is not browser-compatible (MJPEG or something)\n2. The video is 0 bytes initially (generated but empty)3. Some other browser-specific issue\n\nLet me check the video file more carefully. Let me try to see if the video can be played with opencv-python generated content.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be simpler - the synthetic video was generated with OpenCV which creates Motion JPEG (MJPEG) AVI files renamed to MP4. \n\nI need to verify what codec the video actually uses.","thinkingSignature":"549194abf0590e6f4a99cecb41dd248b99e2b25b0e0361700cd59572e092a9f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mn3t5zsipv7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport struct\ndata = open('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/demo.mp4','rb').read()\n# Parse ftyp box to get codec info\ni = 0\nwhile i < len(data) and i + 8 <= len(data):\n    sz = struct.unpack('>I',data[i:i+4])[0]\n    nm = data[i+4:i+8].decode('ascii', errors='?')\n    if sz == 0: sz = len(data) - i\n    if sz < 8: break\n    if nm == 'ftyp':\n        brand = data[i+8:i+12].decode('ascii', errors='?')\n        minor = struct.unpack('>I', data[i+12:i+16])[0]\n        comp = [data[i+16+j:i+20+j].decode('ascii',errors='?') for j in range(0, min(sz-16, 16), 4)]\n        print(f'Brand: {brand}, Minor: {minor}, Compat: {comp}')\n    if nm == 'moov':\n        # parse mvhd\n        mvhd_off = i + 8\n        if data[mvhd_off:mvhd_off+4].decode('ascii',errors='?') == 'mvhd':\n            ver = data[mvhd_off+4]\n            print(f'MVHD version: {ver}')\n    i += sz if sz else 8\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":517,"cacheRead":55488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56005,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792380755,"responseId":"0636e63dc5b8b8611583a2d01e5faf65"}}
