{"type":"message","id":"c575005e","parentId":"c7e37de9","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:27:01.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found `mp4v` codec - this is MPEG-4 Part 2 video. This is technically playable in some browsers but not universally supported. Let me check if it's actually MPEG-4 Part 2 ASP (Simple Profile) or just raw mp4v data.\n\nActually, the codec `mp4v` is NOT well-supported in modern browsers. Chrome/Firefox dropped support for MPEG-4 Part 2 video in many cases. This is likely why the video doesn't play in the browser.\n\nI need to re-generate the video with a browser-compatible codec. Since I can't use ffmpeg (not installed), I need to use another approach.\n\n\nLet me see what video tools I have available on the system.","thinkingSignature":"7967c5eea65f63131632663e5d9b9975984bdd2b8959a41f092a9dffa0dd61a5"},{"type":"text","text":"Video codec là `mp4v` (MPEG-4 Part 2) — **không supported** bởi trình duyệt. Cần re-generate video với codec H.264:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7l6v1yjz2egk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try to find any video encoding tools\nfor cmd in avconv mencoder libav-tools vlc cvlc ogmtools mpeg2enc x264 ffmpeg2theora; do\n  which $cmd 2>/dev/null && echo \"FOUND: $cmd\"\ndone\necho \"---\"\n# Check if opencv-python can encode H.264\npython3 -c \"import cv2; print(cv2.getBuildInformation())\" 2>/dev/null | grep -i \"ffmpeg\\|video\\|codec\\|h.264\" | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":135,"output":348,"cacheRead":56528,"cacheWrite":835,"totalTokens":57846,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792413721,"responseId":"0636e65eec60226a136b110b6e1e358b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f41e95d4","parentId":"c575005e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:27:02.294Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7l6v1yjz2egk_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n    Linker flags (Release):      -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippicv.a -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippiw.a -L/ffmpeg_build/lib  -Wl,--gc-sections -Wl,--as-needed -Wl,--no-undefined  \n    Linker flags (Debug):        -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippicv.a -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippiw.a -L/ffmpeg_build/lib  -Wl,--gc-sections -Wl,--as-needed -Wl,--no-undefined  \n    To be built:                 calib3d core dnn features2d flann gapi highgui imgcodecs imgproc ml objdetect photo python3 stitching video videoio\n  Video I/O:\n    FFMPEG:                      YES\n      avcodec:                   YES (62.11.100)\n    v4l/v4l2:                    YES (linux/videodev2.h)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":365,"aggregated":"---\n    Linker flags (Release):      -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippicv.a -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippiw.a -L/ffmpeg_build/lib  -Wl,--gc-sections -Wl,--as-needed -Wl,--no-undefined  \n    Linker flags (Debug):        -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippicv.a -Wl,--exclude-libs,libippiw.a -L/ffmpeg_build/lib  -Wl,--gc-sections -Wl,--as-needed -Wl,--no-undefined  \n    To be built:                 calib3d core dnn features2d flann gapi highgui imgcodecs imgproc ml objdetect photo python3 stitching video videoio\n  Video I/O:\n    FFMPEG:                      YES\n      avcodec:                   YES (62.11.100)\n    v4l/v4l2:                    YES (linux/videodev2.h)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776792422288}}
{"type":"message","id":"e83e8040","parentId":"f41e95d4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:27:09.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OpenCV has FFMPEG support with `avcodec: YES`. So OpenCV can encode video using FFMPEG's libraries. But the `cv2.VideoWriter` API uses specific codecs. Let me try to use the FFMPEG backend with a proper H.264 encoding.\n\nThe key is to use `cv2.VideoWriter` with the FFMPEG backend and specify H.264 codec. The FourCC code for H.264 through FFmpeg is `'H264'` or `'avc1'`. But in OpenCV, the FourCC is just a 4-character code.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Since OpenCV has FFMPEG built in, I can try to use `cv2.VideoWriter` with `fourcc=cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'H264')` or `fourcc=cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*'avc1')`.\n\n\nLet me test which codec option works best for H.264 encoding.","thinkingSignature":"7283d5c5d7131f148e26e135a81d368b63c669cc37f5950019105924d03e7410"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_px5y1jkrhgtz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2, numpy as np, os\n\n# Check available H.264-compatible codecs in OpenCV via FFmpeg\nfor codec in ['H264', 'avc1', 'X264', 'x264', 'mp4v', 'H265']:\n    try:\n        fourcc = cv2.VideoWriter_fourcc(*codec)\n        print(f'  fourcc {codec}: {fourcc}')\n    except:\n        print(f'  ERROR: {codec}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":243,"output":341,"cacheRead":57100,"cacheWrite":714,"totalTokens":58398,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776792422299,"responseId":"0636e6672d715e05c889b5c5bae2c331"}}
