{"type":"message","id":"3ac27a45","parentId":"684b27aa","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:27:24.792Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"XVID works! XVID is an MPEG-4 Part 2 codec, which should be more compatible than mp4v but still might not work in all browsers. Let me try XVID and see if it works.Actually, the issue is that the current video has `mp4v` codec which is not browser-compatible. XVID might also not be browser-compatible since it's also MPEG-4 Part 2.Let me check what codecs Chrome actually supports:\n- H.264 (avc1) - ✅ supported\n- VP8 - ✅ supported\n- VP9 - ✅ supported\n- MPEG-4 Part 2 (mp4v, Xvid, DivX) - ❌ NOT supported in modern Chrome\n\n\nSince H.264 hardware encoding isn't available and ffmpeg isn't installed, I'm exploring other options like generating WebM video with VP8 or VP9 codecs through Python, or finding alternative ffmpeg packages that might work on this system.\n\nI'm also considering whether ffmpeg could be installed as a Python package via pip, since we have avcodec available through OpenCV's FFMPEG support.","thinkingSignature":"dad068d820db3814fe539d1708f3ed6c0d44732741a388f01074dbc8c9bfc283"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7vdd7xj6e3u3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport subprocess, sys\n\n# Check if we can invoke ffmpeg via the Python av library\ntry:\n    import av\n    print('PyAV available, version:', av.__version__)\n    print('Build info:', hasattr(av, '__ffmpeg_version__'))\nexcept: print('No PyAV')\n\n# Check what's in the ffmpeg_build lib directory mentioned in OpenCV\nimport glob\nlibs = glob.glob('/ffmpeg_build/lib/*.so*')[:10]\nprint('FFmpeg libs:', [l.split('/')[-1] for l in libs])\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":391,"output":385,"cacheRead":58020,"cacheWrite":733,"totalTokens":59529,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolU