{"type":"message","id":"bc9df14e","parentId":"d36714a2","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:29:02.092Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Everything works! The dashboard is at 200, the video is at 200. The user might be accessing a stale URL or their browser has a cached old URL. \n\nBut wait - the user is sending the 404 page content. This is the Flask/Werkzeug 404 page. So somehow the Flask app is serving HTML. But Flask is on port 5000...\n\nOH WAIT. The user's message has timestamp 17:21 UTC, and I restarted the frontend at around 17:26. So the user might have accessed the page at 17:21 BEFORE my latest changes. That's a message that arrived late.\n\nBut also - looking at the 404 response, it's \"404 Not Found\" from \"Werkzeug/3.1.8 Python/3.10.12\" - this is definitely Flask's error page. But the server on port 3003 is Vite/Node...\n \nI need to figure out why Flask's 404 page is showing up at the 3003 port. Either there's a reverse proxy routing requests from 3003 to Flask somewhere, or maybe the user is actually hitting port 5000 instead, or the message timestamp is just misleading and the request happened after my changes.\n\nActually, the timestamp in the message is from 17:21 UTC, which is before my restart at 17:26, so this is an old message. The current system should be working fine now - I should tell the user to try refreshing at http://103.253.21.139:3003 and let me know if they're still having trouble.","thinkingSignature":"fbf879fe9afc09835bece3d8616ba9ec134bca26cf1069ac5961303ef343c3ec"},{"type":"text","text":"Hai service đều đang chạy, dashboard 200, video 200. Tin nhắn của bạn lúc 17:21 UTC — có thể là trước khi fix xong.\n\n**Thử lại:** http://103.253.21.139:3003\n\nNếu vẫn lỗi, cho mình xem browser console (F12 → Console) xem báo gì."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":130,"output":430,"cacheRead":60439,"cacheWrite":407,"totalTokens":61406,"cost":{"input"