{"type":"message","id":"40ff736a","parentId":"39d93856","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:30:06.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but I also need to think about CORS. The video from test-videos.co.uk - when loaded as a video source from the dashboard at 103.253.21.139:3003, the browser will make a cross-origin request to test-videos.co.uk. If test-videos.co.uk doesn't send CORS headers, the canvas toDataURL won't work (for drawing on canvas). But the video element itself should display fine.\n\nActually, looking at the current code - the video element just displays the video. The canvas overlay is removed (we simplified VideoPlayer to not use canvas). So CORS shouldn't matter for the video display.\n\n\nThe annotated frame comes from the backend's /api/frame endpoint on the same origin, so that's fine too. Let me verify the changes work and consider whether the cartoon video will produce meaningful PPE detection results. The detection relies on skin color and helmet-like regions, so it might flag things in the cartoon, but it's not ideal. I should check if there are construction or crowd videos available that would be more appropriate for PPE detection.\n\nLet me scan through some other test video URLs to see if any construction-related content works better.","thinkingSignature":"b20eccad387f3524b259546768ce23f461f9e2ee48d16e6a69bf39bdcb553524"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5t02u9mvihbr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try more video URLs\nfor url in \\\n  \"https://test-videos.co.uk/vids/sintel/mp4/h264/720/Sintel_720_10s_1MB.mp4\" \\\n  \"https://test-videos.co.uk/vids/jellyfish/mp4/h264/720/Jellyfish_720_10s_1MB.mp4\" \\\n  \"http://commondatastorage.googleapis.com/gtv-videos-bucket/sample/ForBiggerBlazes.mp4\"; do\n  code=$(curl -sI -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" --max-time 5 \"$url\")\n  echo \"$code  $(echo $url | grep -o '[^/]*\\.mp4' | head -1)\"\ndone","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages