{"type":"message","id":"014687a7","parentId":"4719d27d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:31:19.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Google storage URLs all return 403 now. Let me use the test-videos.co.uk Big Buck Bunny URL since it works. The user wanted an online URL, and this is a reliable one.\n\nActually, the Big Buck Bunny is cartoon - the PPE detection won't show meaningful results on cartoon characters. Let me think about what the user really needs.\n\nThe user wants a working video demo. Let me:\n1. Use the Big Buck Bunny URL which is confirmed working\n2. Explain that the detection results on cartoon may not be meaningful\n3. For a real demo, they'd need either their own video file or a video showing real people\n\nLet me also update the text in the dashboard to say \"Demo Video (online)\" since it's an online URL.\n\n\nI'm noticing some other video sources that might work better - there's an oceans video from zencdn and a sintel trailer from w3.org - but I should stick with Big Buck Bunny since it's the most reliable option right now.\n\nActually, I realize the user specifically asked for a public online URL and the Big Buck Bunny from test-videos.co.uk fits that perfectly. The cartoon format actually doesn't matter much for a demo since the detection algorithm will just process whatever's in the frame - it'll detect skin-colored regions and other shapes regardless of whether it's animated or real footage. Let me update the dashboard with this URL.","thinkingSignature":"36b0152eed54ba7140f6a3286c2454c6c5f46fcfa8c7dcfe0e136904afaa9435"},{"type":"text","text":"✅ **Xong!** Video giờ dùng link public từ internet (Big Buck Bunny - H.264, chạy được trên mọi trình duyệt).\n\nVào **http://103.253.21.139:3003** nhé!\n\n> ⚠️ **Lưu ý:** Đây là video cartoon — thuật toán detection sẽ vẫn chạy nhưng kết quả trên cartoon không phản ánh năng lực thật. Nếu bạn có video construction thực tế (upload lên server hoặc cho link public), h