{"type":"message","id":"14688423","parentId":"0a0fdd0a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T17:31:35.808Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says the video is returning 206 Partial Content (which means it's being served correctly with Range request support), but it's not displaying. The video is accessible (206) but not showing. The issue might be that the browser needs the video to be loaded in a specific way, or there might be a MIME type issue, or the video element is somehow not rendering.\n\nLet me think about what could cause a video to return 206 but not display:\n1. The video codec might still be an issue\n2. The video element might have some CSS issue\n3. There might be a CORS issue with the video source\n4. The video might be loading but the `<video>` element is hidden\n\n\n5. The video might be returning the wrong content type for the MIME type, or the source is pointing to the wrong URL entirely\n6. The video content itself could be corrupted or in an unsupported format\n\nLet me verify what MIME type is actually being served and whether the video is in the correct format for playback.","thinkingSignature":"d61e21d40cac10dbb4a0641d93bdf68b1af21031cbce7d66aba95a6e3ec7aea6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fbcgntmwb9my_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check MIME type and full headers\ncurl -sI \"http://103.253.21.139:3003/video/demo.mp4\" | head -15\necho \"---\"\n# Check file format\npython3 -c \"\nimport struct\ndata = open('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/demo.mp4','rb').read()\nprint(f'Size: {len(data)} bytes')\nprint(f'First bytes: {data[:20].hex()}')\nprint(f'Is MP4: {data[:4] in (b\\\"ftyp\\\",\\\"\\\\x00\\\\x00\\\\x00\\\")}')\n# find codec\nimport re\nfor pat in [b'avc1', b'mp4v', b'mjpeg', b'H264', b'h264']:\n    idx = data.find(pat)\n    if idx >= 0: print(f'Found codec marker {pat}: offset {idx}')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider"