{"type":"message","id":"af78fa09","parentId":"fd0d9250","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:01:36.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but the user previously couldn't load /video/demo.mp4. Let me think...The issue was:1. `/video` proxy in vite.config was forwarding to Flask2. Flask's `/video` route returned 404 (because I changed it to `/media`)3. After removing the proxy, the video served correctly (200)But the user still reported the video loading error. The issue was the H.264 codec from OpenCV VideoWriter wasn't working (moov at end). Now with ffmpeg encoding, the video is properly H.264 with moov first.Let me also remove the /video proxy from vite.config just to be sure, and rebuild.","thinkingSignature":"ef36695b3d255570d1e026fbcb2d9ef218db3eb3fd4461a4eb955bbec712b166"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x6ydwev753pc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/vite.config.js","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":77,"output":195,"cacheRead":80394,"cacheWrite":444,"totalTokens":81110,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776794490077,"responseId":"0636ee7b45ff772b196e909cee391ae5"}}
