{"type":"message","id":"6ca0fac0","parentId":"6b1e5fd5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:11:19.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is trying to upload a video file, and the browser is trying to load `/tmp/uploaded_...mp4` directly. This is because the frontend's `handleUpload` function creates a blob URL (`URL.createObjectURL(file)`) and passes it as `video_path`, but the frontend is still trying to load it as a regular URL.\n\nWait, looking at the code, when the upload succeeds, `onUpload(data.video_path)` is called. But the backend returns the server-side path like `/tmp/uploaded_...mp4`. This path doesn't exist in the Vite/frontend server!\n\nThe issue is that when uploading a video, the backend saves it to `/tmp/` on the server, then returns the path `/tmp/uploaded_...mp4`. But the frontend's `VideoPlayer` tries to set this as the `currentSrc` and load it directly in a `<video>` tag. \n\nThe browser can't access `/tmp/` from the frontend server—that's a server-side path. I could either proxy the uploaded video through the backend like the old Flask route did, or just serve it directly from the frontend's public folder instead of keeping it in `/tmp/`. The simplest approach is to save uploads directly to the frontend's public directory so they're accessible via the `/video/` route.\n\nActually, wait—the user mentioned \"not push to GitLab,\" which means they're okay with local development. I can store uploads in the `public/video/` directory since Vite serves static files from there. So I'll update the upload handler to save to `/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_...mp4` and return the path like `/video/uploaded_...mp4` for the frontend to use.","thinkingSignature":"f2345627785388a7dda2d70cd905c09a7d57ff706171541f1bffa490c1b7eea9"},{"type":"text","text":"Lỗi là vì video upload lưu ở `/tmp/` trên server — browser không truy cập được từ frontend. Fix: lưu vào thư mục public của frontend để Vite serve được.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_62d66uy0wbjs_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/app.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    # Save to /tmp with unique name\n    filename = f\"uploaded_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}_{file.filename}\"\n    tmp_path = os.path.join('/tmp', filename)","newText":"    # Save to frontend public/video/ so Vite can serve it\n    safe_name = file.filename.replace(' ', '_')\n    filename = f\"uploaded_{datetime.now().strftime('%Y%m%d_%H%M%S')}_{safe_name}\"\n    frontend_public = os.path.join(\n        os.path.dirname(os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))),\n        'frontend', 'public', 'video'\n    )\n    os.makedirs(frontend_public, exist_ok=True)\n    tmp_path = os.path.join(frontend_public, filename)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":661,"cacheRead":100618,"cacheWrite":428,"totalTokens":101707,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795061101,"responseId":"0636f0b65c581783be5f9bc1e57a6920"}}
