{"type":"message","id":"b8956a9e","parentId":"3ba198f9","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:14:20.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is reporting two issues:\n1. Uploaded video with only 3 people but the system detected 52 people\n2. The detection doesn't focus on the people correctly\n\nThis is a problem with the Edge+Blob+Color detection algorithm. It's detecting way too many false positives. The issue is that the current algorithm uses OpenCV blob detection + background subtraction which is too sensitive and detects everything - scaffolding, signs, barrels, etc.\n\nThe root problem is that we're using a basic computer vision approach without a real AI model. The detection algorithm detects ANY blob of the right size/color and classifies it as a person, leading to massive false positives.\n\nI need to fix the detection algorithm to be much more conservative:\n\n\n- Increase the minimum area threshold for what counts as a person to filter out scaffolding and other false positives\n- Add more stringent criteria for what constitutes a valid detection\n- Improve the helmet and vest color analysis to reduce false positives\n- Use better motion detection to isolate actual people rather than just any moving or colored region\n\nThe real issue is that the scaffolding and caution tape are being picked up as people because they match the color and size thresholds. I need to make the detection much more conservative by raising the minimum area requirements, adding stricter shape checks, and validating helmet and vest colors more carefully.\n\nNow I'm looking at the detector.py code to identify where these adjustments need to happen.","thinkingSignature":"e1c5135bda55ad7585fa314c35ee1e149c2f3b1cc6d4f7d759103046360dc66d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yc22gh7s11fl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":325,"cacheRead":102357,"cacheWrite":310,"totalTokens":102992,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795249119,"responseId":"0636f17325a593b4f3966502f251e1fc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8ddf5db1","parentId":"b8956a9e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:14:20.428Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_yc22gh7s11fl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nS1 PPE Detection Engine — Edge + Blob + Color Analysis\nNo ML models required. Works on any construction site image.\nPipeline:\n  1. Edge detection → find strong vertical edges\n  2. Blob detection → find person-shaped regions\n  3. Color analysis → classify helmet + vest\n  4. Aspect ratio filtering → reject non-person shapes\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import deque\n\n\nclass PPEDetector:\n    \"\"\"\n    Robust PPE detection using image processing only.\n    Works without internet or model downloads.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        conf_threshold: float = 0.4,\n        min_body_height: int = 60,\n        min_body_width: int = 25,\n        max_body_width: int = 300,\n    ):\n        self.conf_threshold = conf_threshold\n        self.min_body_height = min_body_height\n        self.min_body_width = min_body_width\n        self.max_body_width = max_body_width\n        self._history = deque(maxlen=5)  # For temporal smoothing\n\n    def process_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray):\n        \"\"\"Run detection + draw boxes. Returns (detections, annotated_frame).\"\"\"\n        detections = self.detect_from_frame(frame)\n        annotated = self._annotate(frame.copy(), detections)\n        return detections, annotated\n\n    def _annotate(self, frame, detections):\n        \"\"\"Draw bounding boxes and PPE status on frame.\"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        for d in detections:\n            x1, y1, x2, y2 = d['bbox']\n            x1, y1, x2, y2 = int(x1), int(y1), int(x2), int(y2)\n            ppe = d['ppe_status']\n            ok = ppe.get('compliant', False)\n            col = (0, 200, 83) if ok else (255, 23, 68)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), col, 2)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), col, -1)\n            label = 'OK' if ok else f\"{'NO-HELMET ' if not ppe.get('has_helmet') else ''}{'NO-VEST' if not ppe.get('has_vest') else ''}\".strip()\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1 - 22), (x1 + len(label) * 8 + 10, y1), (0, 0, 0), -1)\n            cv2.putText(frame, label, (x1 + 5, y1 - 7), cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.5, col, 1)\n        return frame\n\n    def detect_from_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Full detection pipeline on a single frame.\n        Returns list of person detections with PPE status.\n        \"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n\n        # Step 1: Find potential person regions using multi-scale blob detection\n        regions = self._find_person_blobs(frame)\n\n        # Step 2: Analyze each region for PPE\n        detections = []\n        for (bx1, by1, bw, bh) in regions:\n            bx2, by2 = bx1 + bw, by1 + bh\n\n            # PPE analysis\n            ppe = self._analyze_ppe(frame, bx1, by1, bx2, by2, bw, bh)\n\n            # Confidence from detection quality + PPE confidence\n            area_ratio = (bw * bh) / max(w * h, 1)\n            size_score = min(area_ratio * 10, 0.4)\n            ppe_score = 0.3 if ppe[\"has_helmet\"] and ppe[\"has_vest\"] else 0.2\n            conf = min(0.3 + size_score + ppe_score + 0.1, 0.92)\n\n            detections.append({\n                \"bbox\": [float(bx1), float(by1), float(bx2), float(by2)],\n                \"confidence\": round(conf, 3),\n                \"class_id\": 0,\n                \"class_name\": \"person\",\n                \"ppe_status\": {\n                    \"has_helmet\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"],\n                    \"has_vest\": ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                    \"compliant\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"] and ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                },\n                \"width\": float(bw),\n                \"height\": float(bh),\n                \"center_x\": float(bx1 + bw / 2),\n                \"center_y\": float(by1 + bh / 2),\n            })\n\n        return detections\n\n    def _find_person_blobs(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list:\n        \"\"\"\n        Find person-shaped regions using edge + contour analysis.\n        \"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n        # ── Multi-scale processing ──────────────────────────────────────────\n        all_blobs = []\n\n        for scale in [1.0, 0.75, 0.5]:\n            if scale != 1.0:\n                nh, nw = int(h * scale), int(w * scale)\n                g = cv2.resize(gray, (nw, nh))\n                frm = cv2.resize(frame, (nw, nh))\n            else:\n                g, frm = gray, frame\n\n            # Background subtraction (simple: difference from blurred)\n            bg = cv2.GaussianBlur(g, (31, 31), 0)\n            diff = cv2.absdiff(g, bg)\n            _, fg = cv2.threshold(diff, 15, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n\n            # Morphological cleanup\n            kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n            fg = cv2.morphologyEx(fg, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n            fg = cv2.morphologyEx(fg, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n\n            # Edge detection for additional blob finding\n            edges = cv2.Canny(g, 40, 120)\n            edges = cv2.dilate(edges, kernel, iterations=1)\n\n            # Combine foreground + edges\n            combined = cv2.bitwise_or(fg, edges)\n\n            # Find contours\n            contours, _ = cv2.findContours(combined, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)\n\n            min_h = int(self.min_body_height * scale)\n            min_w = int(self.min_body_width * scale)\n            max_w = int(self.max_body_width * scale)\n\n            for cnt in contours:\n                x, y, cw, ch = cv2.boundingRect(cnt)\n                area = cw * ch\n                if area < min_w * min_h:\n                    continue\n                if ch < min_h:\n                    continue\n                if cw < min_w or cw > max_w:\n                    continue\n\n                # Aspect ratio: person is taller than wide\n                aspect = ch / max(cw, 1)\n                if aspect < 1.1:  # Too square\n                    continue\n\n                # Solidity: fill ratio should be reasonable\n                hull = cv2.convexHull(cnt)\n                hull_area = cv2.contourArea(hull)\n                solidity = area / max(hull_area, 1)\n                if solidity < 0.15:  # Too sparse\n                    continue\n\n                # Convert back to original scale\n                sx = int(x / scale)\n                sy = int(y / scale)\n                sw = int(cw / scale)\n                sh = int(ch / scale)\n\n                all_blobs.append((sx, sy, sw, sh))\n\n        # ── Non-Maximum Suppression ─────────────────────────────────────────\n        blobs = self._merge_blobs(all_blobs)\n        return blobs\n\n    def _analyze_ppe(\n        self, frame: np.ndarray,\n        bx1: int, by1: int, bx2: int, by2: int, bw: int, bh: int\n    ) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Analyze helmet and vest presence using color analysis.\"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        bx1, by1 = max(0, bx1), max(0, by1)\n        bx2 = min(w, bx2)\n        by2 = min(h, by2)\n\n        body_roi = frame[by1:by2, bx1:bx2]\n        if body_roi.size == 0:\n            return {\"has_helmet\": True, \"has_vest\": True}\n\n        gray_roi = cv2.cvtColor(body_roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        hsv_roi = cv2.cvtColor(body_roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\n        has_helmet = False\n        has_vest = False\n\n        # ── Helmet: top 20-25% of body box ─────────────────────────────────\n        helmet_bottom = by1 + int(bh * 0.25)\n        helmet_top = by1\n        if helmet_bottom > helmet_top:\n            helmet_roi = frame[helmet_top:helmet_bottom, bx1:bx2]\n            if helmet_roi.size > 0:\n                has_helmet = self._detect_helmet(helmet_roi)\n\n        # ── Vest: middle 30-75% of body box ────────────────────────────────\n        vest_top = by1 + int(bh * 0.30)\n        vest_bot = by1 + int(bh * 0.75)\n        if vest_bot > vest_top:\n            vest_roi = frame[vest_top:vest_bot, bx1:bx2]\n            if vest_roi.size > 0:\n                has_vest = self._detect_vest(vest_roi)\n\n        return {\n            \"has_helmet\": has_helmet,\n            \"has_vest\": has_vest,\n            \"compliant\": has_helmet and has_vest,\n        }\n\n    def _detect_helmet(self, roi: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Detect helmet colors in head region.\"\"\"\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n        # Safety helmet: yellow, orange, white\n        # Widen ranges to handle JPEG compression artifacts\n        ranges = [\n            ([5, 25, 50],  [45, 255, 255]),   # Yellow (BGR: yellow → H~30)\n            ([0, 35, 55],  [25, 255, 255]),   # Orange\n            ([0, 0, 175],  [180, 25, 255]),  # White/bright\n        ]\n        for lower, upper in ranges:\n            mask = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array(lower), np.array(upper))\n            ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n            if ratio > 0.05:\n                return True\n        return False\n\n    def _detect_vest(self, roi: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Detect safety vest colors (fluorescent + reflective).\"\"\"\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\n        # Fluorescent vest colors (widen for JPEG)\n        vest_ranges = [\n            ([5, 25, 60],  [45, 255, 255]),  # Yellow-green\n            ([0, 35, 60],  [25, 255, 255]),  # Orange\n            ([0, 20, 75],  [30, 255, 255]),  # Orange-yellow\n        ]\n        for lower, upper in vest_ranges:\n            mask = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array(lower), np.array(upper))\n            ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n            if ratio > 0.06:\n                return True\n\n        # Reflective stripes (high brightness, low saturation)\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        _, bright = cv2.threshold(gray, 180, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n        bright_ratio = cv2.countNonZero(bright) / max(bright.size, 1)\n        if bright_ratio > 0.12:\n            return True\n\n        return False\n\n    def _merge_blobs(self, blobs: list, iou_thresh: float = 0.3) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Merge overlapping blob detections.\"\"\"\n        if not blobs:\n            return []\n        boxes = np.array(blobs, dtype=float)\n        x1, y1 = boxes[:, 0], boxes[:, 1]\n        x2, y2 = boxes[:, 0] + boxes[:, 2], boxes[:, 1] + boxes[:, 3]\n        areas = boxes[:, 2] * boxes[:, 3]\n        order = areas.argsort()[::-1]\n\n        keep = []\n        while order.size > 0:\n            i = order[0]\n            keep.append(tuple(boxes[i].astype(int)))\n            if order.size == 1:\n                break\n            xx1 = np.maximum(x1[i], x1[order[1:]])\n            yy1 = np.maximum(y1[i], y1[order[1:]])\n            xx2 = np.minimum(x2[i], x2[order[1:]])\n            yy2 = np.minimum(y2[i], y2[order[1:]])\n            inter = np.maximum(0, xx2 - xx1) * np.maximum(0, yy2 - yy1)\n            iou = inter / (areas[i] + areas[order[1:]] - inter + 1e-6)\n            inds = np.where(iou <= iou_thresh)[0]\n            order = order[inds + 1]\n        return keep\n\n    def get_violations(self, detections: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n        return [d for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"compliant\", True)]\n\n    def get_summary(self, detections: list[dict]) -> dict:\n        total = len(detections)\n        compliant = sum(1 for d in detections if d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"compliant\", True))\n        violations = total - compliant\n        no_helmet = sum(1 for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"has_helmet\", True))\n        no_vest = sum(1 for d in detections if not d.get(\"ppe_status\", {}).get(\"has_vest\", True))\n        return {\n            \"total_persons\": total,\n            \"compliant\": compliant,\n            \"violations\": violations,\n            \"no_helmet\": no_helmet,\n            \"no_vest\": no_vest,\n            \"compliance_rate\": round(compliant / total * 100, 1) if total > 0 else 100.0,\n        }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    detector = PPEDetector()\n    print(f\"PPEDetector ready (Edge+Blob+Color)\")\n    print(\"Usage: detector.detect_from_frame(frame) → list[detections]\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795260405}}
{"type":"message","id":"99306d86","parentId":"8ddf5db1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:15:16.233Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full detector. The problem is in `_find_person_blobs`. The algorithm is too aggressive:\n\n1. Multi-scale processing creates duplicates\n2. The solidity threshold is too low (0.15)\n3. The minimum area threshold is too low (60x25 = 1500 pixels)\n4. The aspect ratio threshold is too low (1.1)\n5. Background subtraction + edges picks up too many things (scaffolding, caution tape, barrels)\n\nI need to significantly tighten the detection:\n1. Increase minimum body height from 60 to 120 pixels (for 720p video, a person should be at least 120px tall)\n\n\n2. Raise the solidity threshold to 0.4 to filter out scaffolding\n3. Tighten the aspect ratio to 1.5 so only clearly vertical shapes are detected\n4. Remove the multi-scale processing that generates too many duplicates\n5. Boost the confidence threshold to 0.5 to only keep reliable detections\n6. Use motion detection to isolate actual moving people from static background elements\n\nFor background subtraction, I should switch to MOG2 instead of the simple blurred difference approach, and prioritize skin tone detection as a person indicator. The current algorithm is generating way too many false positives—52 detections from just 3 people is completely wrong, and it's picking up scaffolding and caution tape as people. I need to fundamentally rework the detection pipeline with much stricter constraints on body dimensions, shape ratios, and how I'm combining edge detection with foreground masking.","thinkingSignature":"bd788219fac71a81ed1a1ef62d8eb5fe1f43c9441d3f86655c95ffc811c3c9af"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm ra ngay! Thuật toán hiện tại quá nhạy — detect cả scaffolding, thùng, biển báo thành \"người\". Viết lại thuật toán hoàn toàn:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7t1qmy9ldpvy_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","content":"\"\"\"\nS1 PPE Detection Engine v2 — Improved Edge + Shape + Color Analysis\nFixes: too many false positives (scaffolding, barrels, signs)\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import deque\n\n\nclass PPEDetector:\n    \"\"\"\n    Improved PPE detection using stricter shape + skin tone analysis.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        min_body_height: int = 80,\n        min_body_width: int = 30,\n        max_body_width: int = 200,\n        min_area: int = 8000,\n        conf_threshold: float = 0.45,\n    ):\n        self.min_body_height = min_body_height\n        self.min_body_width = min_body_width\n        self.max_body_width = max_body_width\n        self.min_area = min_area\n        self.conf_threshold = conf_threshold\n        self._bg_subtractor = cv2.createBackgroundSubtractorMOG2(\n            history=30, varThreshold=40, detectShadows=False\n        )\n        self._history = deque(maxlen=5)\n\n    def process_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray):\n        detections = self.detect_from_frame(frame)\n        annotated = self._annotate(frame.copy(), detections)\n        return detections, annotated\n\n    def _annotate(self, frame, detections):\n        for d in detections:\n            x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in d['bbox']]\n            ppe = d['ppe_status']\n            ok = ppe.get('compliant', False)\n            col = (0, 200, 83) if ok else (255, 23, 68)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), col, 2)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (col[0]//3, col[1]//3, col[2]//3), -1)\n            label = 'OK' if ok else (\n                'NO-HELMET' if not ppe.get('has_helmet') and not ppe.get('has_vest')\n                else 'NO-HELMET' if not ppe.get('has_helmet')\n                else 'NO-VEST'\n            )\n            lw = len(label) * 8 + 12\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, max(0, y1 - 24)), (x1 + lw, y1), (0, 0, 0), -1)\n            cv2.putText(frame, label, (x1 + 6, y1 - 8),\n                cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.48, col, 1)\n        return frame\n\n    def detect_from_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]:\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n\n        # Step 1: Get motion/foreground regions (strict)\n        motion_mask = self._get_foreground(frame)\n\n        # Step 2: Find skin-toned regions (people have visible skin)\n        skin_mask = self._detect_skin(frame)\n\n        # Step 3: Combine — must have BOTH motion AND skin (or strong motion)\n        combined = cv2.bitwise_and(motion_mask, skin_mask)\n        # Also keep strong motion-only regions (when person is fully clothed)\n        strong_motion = cv2.threshold(motion_mask, 200, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)[1]\n        combined = cv2.bitwise_or(combined, strong_motion)\n\n        # Step 4: Find contours from combined mask\n        contours, _ = cv2.findContours(combined, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)\n\n        detections = []\n        for cnt in contours:\n            x, y, cw, ch = cv2.boundingRect(cnt)\n            area = cw * ch\n            # ── Strict size filtering ────────────────────────────────────\n            if area < self.min_area:\n                continue\n            if ch < self.min_body_height or cw < self.min_body_width:\n                continue\n            if cw > self.max_body_width or ch > h * 0.9:\n                continue\n\n            # ── Aspect ratio: person is 2-5x taller than wide ───────────\n            aspect = ch / max(cw, 1)\n            if aspect < 1.4 or aspect > 8:\n                continue\n\n            # ── Solidity check: person is compact, not sparse ───────────\n            hull = cv2.convexHull(cnt)\n            hull_area = cv2.contourArea(hull)\n            solidity = area / max(hull_area, 1)\n            if solidity < 0.35:\n                continue\n\n            # ── Position check: person should be near ground ─────────────\n            # Reject objects in upper 15% (likely signs, sky elements)\n            if y < h * 0.15 and ch < h * 0.4:\n                continue\n\n            # ── Edge density check: real people have structured edges ─────\n            roi = frame[y:y+ch, x:x+cw]\n            if roi.size == 0:\n                continue\n            gray_roi = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n            edges = cv2.Canny(gray_roi, 50, 150)\n            edge_density = cv2.countNonZero(edges) / max(edges.size, 1)\n            # People have structured edges (clothing, limbs), not too sparse or dense\n            if edge_density < 0.05 or edge_density > 0.55:\n                continue\n\n            # ── Color variance: person has varied colors, not uniform ─────\n            std = np.std(gray_roi)\n            if std < 8:\n                continue\n\n            # This looks like a person — analyze PPE\n            bx1, by1, bx2, by2 = x, y, x+cw, y+ch\n            ppe = self._analyze_ppe(frame, bx1, by1, bx2, by2, cw, ch)\n\n            # Confidence\n            conf = min(0.45 + solidity * 0.2 + (ch / h) * 0.15, 0.88)\n            if not ppe[\"has_helmet\"] and not ppe[\"has_vest\"]:\n                conf *= 0.85  # Penalize fully non-PPE\n\n            detections.append({\n                \"bbox\": [float(bx1), float(by1), float(bx2), float(by2)],\n                \"confidence\": round(conf, 3),\n                \"class_id\": 0,\n                \"class_name\": \"person\",\n                \"ppe_status\": {\n                    \"has_helmet\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"],\n                    \"has_vest\": ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                    \"compliant\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"] and ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                },\n                \"width\": float(cw),\n                \"height\": float(ch),\n                \"center_x\": float(bx1 + cw / 2),\n                \"center_y\": float(by1 + ch / 2),\n            })\n\n        # ── Merge overlapping detections ────────────────────────────────────\n        detections = self._nms(detections)\n        return detections\n\n    def _get_foreground(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get foreground mask using MOG2 background subtraction.\"\"\"\n        fg_mask = self._bg_subtractor.apply(frame, learningRate=0.01)\n        # Clean up\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        fg_mask = cv2.morphologyEx(fg_mask, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n        fg_mask = cv2.morphologyEx(fg_mask, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return fg_mask\n\n    def _detect_skin(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Detect skin-colored pixels in YCrCb + HSV space.\"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        ycrcb = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YCrCb)\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\n        # YCrCb skin ranges\n        skin1 = cv2.inRange(ycrcb, np.array([0, 133, 77]), np.array([255, 173, 127]))\n        # HSV skin ranges\n        skin2 = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 20, 70]), np.array([17, 255, 255]))\n\n        skin = cv2.bitwise_or(skin1, skin2)\n\n        # Dilate to connect nearby skin pixels\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (7, 7))\n        skin = cv2.dilate(skin, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return skin\n\n    def _analyze_ppe(\n        self, frame: np.ndarray,\n        bx1: int, by1: int, bx2: int, by2: int,\n        bw: int, bh: int\n    ) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Analyze helmet and vest presence in detected region.\"\"\"\n        fh, fw = frame.shape[:2]\n        bx1, by1 = max(0, bx1), max(0, by1)\n        bx2, by2 = min(fw, bx2), min(fh, by2)\n\n        body = frame[by1:by2, bx1:bx2]\n        if body.size == 0:\n            return {\"has_helmet\": True, \"has_vest\": True, \"compliant\": True}\n\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(body, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(body, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n        has_helmet = False\n        has_vest = False\n\n        # ── HELMET: top 18% of bounding box ──────────────────────────────\n        helmet_end = int(bh * 0.18)\n        if helmet_end > 5:\n            helmet_roi = body[:helmet_end, :]\n            helmet_hsv = hsv[:helmet_end, :]\n            has_helmet = self._check_helmet(helmet_roi, helmet_hsv)\n\n        # ── VEST: middle 25-70% of bounding box ─────────────────────────\n        vest_top = int(bh * 0.25)\n        vest_bot = int(bh * 0.70)\n        if vest_bot > vest_top:\n            vest_roi = body[vest_top:vest_bot, :]\n            vest_hsv = hsv[vest_top:vest_bot, :]\n            has_vest = self._check_vest(vest_roi, vest_hsv)\n\n        return {\n            \"has_helmet\": has_helmet,\n            \"has_vest\": has_vest,\n            \"compliant\": has_helmet and has_vest,\n        }\n\n    def _check_helmet(self, roi: np.ndarray, hsv: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Helmet: yellow/orange/white in upper head region.\"\"\"\n        if roi.size == 0 or hsv.size == 0:\n            return False\n        h, w = roi.shape[:2]\n        if h < 5 or w < 5:\n            return False\n\n        # Yellow helmet: H 20-35 in OpenCV (0-180)\n        mask_y = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([15, 30, 60]), np.array([40, 255, 255]))\n        # Orange helmet\n        mask_o = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 40, 60]), np.array([18, 255, 255]))\n        # White helmet (pure white top)\n        mask_w = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 0, 160]), np.array([180, 30, 255]))\n        # Blue helmet (common in some sites)\n        mask_b = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([90, 30, 50]), np.array([130, 255, 255]))\n        # Red helmet\n        mask_r = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 40, 50]), np.array([10, 255, 255]))\n\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask_y, mask_o)\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask, mask_w)\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask, mask_b)\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask, mask_r)\n\n        ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n        return ratio > 0.08  # helmet must cover >8% of head region\n\n    def _check_vest(self, roi: np.ndarray, hsv: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Vest: orange/yellow fluorescent OR reflective white stripes.\"\"\"\n        if roi.size == 0 or hsv.size == 0:\n            return False\n        h, w = roi.shape[:2]\n        if h < 5 or w < 5:\n            return False\n\n        # Orange vest\n        mask_o = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 50, 80]), np.array([15, 255, 255]))\n        # Yellow-green vest\n        mask_y = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([20, 40, 80]), np.array([45, 255, 255]))\n        # Lime green\n        mask_l = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([45, 40, 80]), np.array([75, 255, 255]))\n\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask_o, mask_y)\n        mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask, mask_l)\n\n        vest_ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n        if vest_ratio > 0.12:\n            return True\n\n        # Reflective stripes: high brightness, low saturation (white/silver)\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        # Look for horizontal bright bands (reflective stripes)\n        blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(gray, (7, 7), 0)\n        _, bright = cv2.threshold(blur, 200, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n        # Check if there are horizontal bright bands\n        row_sums = bright.sum(axis=1) / 255  # number of white pixels per row\n        # A reflective vest has alternating bright/dark rows\n        if len(row_sums) > 3:\n            transitions = np.abs(np.diff(np.sign(row_sums - w * 0.3)))\n            if np.sum(transitions) >= 2:  # at least 2 transitions = stripes\n                return True\n\n        return False\n\n    def _nms(self, detections: list[dict], iou_thresh: float = 0.35) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"Non-Maximum Suppression for overlapping detections.\"\"\"\n        if not detections:\n            return []\n        boxes = [(d['bbox'][0], d['bbox'][1],\n                  d['bbox'][2]-d['bbox'][0], d['bbox'][3]-d['bbox'][1])\n                 for d in detections]\n        scores = [d['confidence'] for d in detections]\n        indices = self._hard_nms(boxes, scores, iou_thresh)\n        return [detections[i] for i in indices]\n\n    def _hard_nms(self, boxes, scores, thresh):\n        \"\"\"Hard NMS.\"\"\"\n        if not boxes:\n            return []\n        boxes = np.array(boxes, dtype=float)\n        scores = np.array(scores, dtype=float)\n        x1, y1 = boxes[:, 0], boxes[:, 1]\n        x2, y2 = boxes[:, 0] + boxes[:, 2], boxes[:, 1] + boxes[:, 3]\n        areas = boxes[:, 2] * boxes[:, 3]\n        order = scores.argsort()[::-1]\n        keep = []\n        while order.size > 0:\n            i = order[0]\n            keep.append(i)\n            if order.size == 1:\n                break\n            xx1 = np.maximum(x1[i], x1[order[1:]])\n            yy1 = np.maximum(y1[i], y1[order[1:]])\n            xx2 = np.minimum(x2[i], x2[order[1:]])\n            yy2 = np.minimum(y2[i], y2[order[1:]])\n            inter = np.maximum(0, xx2 - xx1) * np.maximum(0, yy2 - yy1)\n            union = areas[i] + areas[order[1:]] - inter\n            iou = inter / np.maximum(union, 1e-6)\n            order = order[1:][iou <= thresh]\n        return keep\n\n    def get_violations(self, detections: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:\n        return [d for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"compliant\"]]\n\n    def get_summary(self, detections: list[dict]) -> dict:\n        total = len(detections)\n        compliant = sum(1 for d in detections if d[\"ppe_status\"][\"compliant\"])\n        violations = total - compliant\n        no_helmet = sum(1 for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"has_helmet\"])\n        no_vest = sum(1 for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"has_vest\"])\n        return {\n            \"total_persons\": total,\n            \"compliant\": compliant,\n            \"violations\": violations,\n            \"no_helmet\": no_helmet,\n            \"no_vest\": no_vest,\n            \"compliance_rate\": round(compliant / total * 100, 1) if total > 0 else 100.0,\n        }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    detector = PPEDetector()\n    print(\"PPEDetector v2 ready (MOG2 + Skin + Shape)\")\n    print(\"Usage: detector.detect_from_frame(frame) -> list[detections]\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3388,"output":4389,"cacheRead":102862,"cacheWrite":98,"totalTokens":110737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795260455,"responseId":"0636f17e61b5acd5c762e00df3e49d4f"}}
