{"type":"message","id":"a83283c6","parentId":"c2b8ba9f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:15:34.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, 0 detections. The MOG2 background subtractor needs some frames to build a background model before it can subtract. Let me check if this is the issue - maybe I need to pre-process some frames through the background subtractor to get it initialized.\n\nActually, the issue might be that the first frame triggers the background subtractor but since there's no history yet, everything is considered foreground. Let me try running a few frames first.","thinkingSignature":"14813afbd4d3c8bf4fa498a24e279b4b40870b6d7aa3f063900ba6b0d7050bc0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9wq799b15sn4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\nframes = []\nwhile len(frames) < 30:\n    ret, frame = cap.read()\n    if not ret: break\n    frames.append(frame)\ncap.release()\n\nprint(f\"Loaded {len(frames)} frames\")\n\n# Feed first 20 frames to build background model\nfor i, f in enumerate(frames[:20]):\n    _ = det._get_foreground(f)\n\n# Now detect on frame 25\nframe = frames[24]\ndets = det.detect_from_frame(frame)\nprint(f\"Detections: {len(dets)}\")\nfor d in dets:\n    x1,y1,x2,y2 = d['bbox']\n    print(f\"  [{x1:.0f},{y1:.0f},{x2:.0f},{y2:.0f}] \"\n          f\"{d['width']:.0f}x{d['height']:.0f} conf={d['confidence']:.2f} \"\n          f\"H={d['ppe_status']['has_helmet']} V={d['ppe_status']['has_vest']}\")\n\nsm = det.get_summary(dets)\nprint(f\"Summary: {sm}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":116,"output":441,"cacheRead":106311,"cacheWrite":4791,"totalTokens":1116