{"type":"message","id":"02fd101b","parentId":"ac186913","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:15:48.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The detector now finds 2 people (correct!) instead of 52. But it only finds 2 out of 4 workers in the synthetic video. Let me check what's happening with the other 2 workers - they might be moving less or have different colors.\n\nActually, looking at the synthetic video - the workers move slowly side to side. The MOG2 background subtractor might not be picking up the ones that are more static. Also, the synthetic video has some limitations with the simple drawn graphics.\n\nLet me also check if the detector needs to warm up for a few frames before getting good results. And let me check how many frames the video processor processes.\n\nActually, the issue is that MOG2 needs a few frames to initialize its background model. \n\nI'm thinking the video processor should handle this warm-up phase automatically, but let me test the detector on a specific frame to see what's actually being detected versus what's in the scene. The background subtractor might be the bottleneck here - it could be missing the workers that don't have much movement or don't stand out visually against the background.","thinkingSignature":"a1d998e034cf4aaac78e30bce1c8f3cf8be077ed084a7dd50e3b416f18276251"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3h9hav4y82oa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\nimport numpy as np\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\n\n# Warm up MOG2 with first 30 frames\nfor i in range(30):\n    ret, _ = cap.read()\n    if not ret: break\n\n# Read and detect frame 35 (should have all 4 workers visible)\nfor i in range(5):\n    ret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\nif ret:\n    print(f\"Frame shape: {frame.shape}\")\n    \n    # Check foreground mask\n    fg = det._get_foreground(frame)\n    fg_pixels = cv2.countNonZero(fg)\n    print(f\"Foreground pixels: {fg_pixels} ({fg_pixels/(frame.shape[0]*frame.shape[1])*100:.1f}%)\")\n    \n    # Check skin mask\n    skin = det._detect_skin(frame)\n    skin_pixels = cv2.countNonZero(skin)\n    print(f\"Skin pixels: {skin_pixels}\")\n    \n    dets = det.detect_from_frame(frame)\n    print(f\"\\nDetections: {len(dets)}\")\n    for d in dets:\n        x1,y1,x2,y2 = d['bbox']\n        print(f\"  [{x1:.0f},{y1:.0f}]-[{x2:.0f},{y2:.0f}] \"\n              f\"conf={d['confidence']:.2f} H={d['ppe_status']['has_helmet']} V={d['ppe_status']['has_vest']}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":156,"output":645,"cacheRead":110743,"cacheWrite":884,"totalTokens":112428,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795335884,"responseId":"0636f1c95a79ae0b32c8cd8d6cba1f3b"}}
