{"type":"message","id":"feeeafcd","parentId":"9f067ac3","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:16:00.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The foreground mask is 100% (everything is foreground) - that's the problem. The MOG2 subtractor isn't working well because:\n1. The synthetic video has very distinct colors from the background (scaffolding is grey, ground is brown, sky is blue)\n2. MOG2 is flagging everything as foreground because the warmup frames don't establish a stable background\n\nI need a different approach. Let me try a different method:1. Instead of background subtraction, use the drawn person's actual colors (skin, clothing colors) to detect them\n2. Use a combination of skin detection + shape detection without background subtractionActually, the issue is that the MOG2 background subtractor is not good for synthetic/animated graphics. \n\nFor this synthetic video, I should drop the background subtraction entirely and rely on skin detection combined with a skin-colored oval/circle finder for the head and a rectangular region below it for the body. But realistically, I need to detect real construction footage from a webcam or uploaded video, not just synthetic graphics. The real problem is that MOG2 produces 100% foreground on synthetic frames because the drawn colors are so distinct from any background model. Let me try a different approach instead.\n\nI'm considering a skin-tone detection method instead—finding skin-colored blobs and checking if they have the right vertical proportions for a person. I could also use motion detection with frame differencing on the synthetic video, or just increase the learning rate of MOG2 and feed it more frames. Actually, a simpler approach would be to drop MOG2 entirely and rely on skin detection for head and face areas, plus a body-shaped rectangle below, combined with color-based PPE detection.","thinkingSignature":"2d95e28122f0c2430f206c1acea9f60a8a50da3d59eeda02b78a02838557ae89"},{"type":"text","text":"MOG2 không hoạt động tốt với video tổng hợp. Thay bằng **Frame Differencing + Skin Detection**:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xkex815nujpp_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"        self._bg_subtractor = cv2.createBackgroundSubtractorMOG2(\n            history=30, varThreshold=40, detectShadows=False\n        )\n        self._history = deque(maxlen=5)","newText":"        self._bg_subtractor = cv2.createBackgroundSubtractorMOG2(\n            history=60, varThreshold=60, detectShadows=False\n        )\n        self._history = deque(maxlen=5)\n        self._prev_gray = None  # For frame differencing"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":84,"output":561,"cacheRead":111181,"cacheWrite":1215,"totalTokens":113041,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795349014,"responseId":"0636f1d6dc5f858b74798270783de1af"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7278dfc7","parentId":"feeeafcd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:16:01.026Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xkex815nujpp_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  25         self.max_body_width = max_body_width\n  26         self.min_area = min_area\n  27         self.conf_threshold = conf_threshold\n  28         self._bg_subtractor = cv2.createBackgroundSubtractorMOG2(\n- 29             history=30, varThreshold=40, detectShadows=False\n+ 29             history=60, varThreshold=60, detectShadows=False\n  30         )\n  31         self._history = deque(maxlen=5)\n+ 32         self._prev_gray = None  # For frame differencing\n  32 \n  33     def process_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray):\n  34         detections = self.detect_from_frame(frame)\n  35         annotated = self._annotate(frame.copy(), detections)\n     ...","firstChangedLine":29},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795360991}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab6d6e2d","parentId":"7278dfc7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:16:09.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the `_get_foreground` method to also use frame differencing in addition to MOG2:","thinkingSignature":"6c038ffd16444a1b56d7a25c9cb910c511daf58ea29118adbc35434f7362d19d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uoyaa5j9xn48_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def _get_foreground(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get foreground mask using MOG2 background subtraction.\"\"\"\n        fg_mask = self._bg_subtractor.apply(frame, learningRate=0.01)\n        # Clean up\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        fg_mask = cv2.morphologyEx(fg_mask, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n        fg_mask = cv2.morphologyEx(fg_mask, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return fg_mask","newText":"    def _get_foreground(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get foreground mask using MOG2 + frame differencing.\"\"\"\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n        # MOG2 background subtraction\n        mog_mask = self._bg_subtractor.apply(frame, learningRate=0.02)\n\n        # Frame differencing (detect motion between consecutive frames)\n        motion_mask = np.zeros_like(gray)\n        if self._prev_gray is not None:\n            diff = cv2.absdiff(gray, self._prev_gray)\n            _, motion = cv2.threshold(diff, 12, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n            # Dilate motion to connect nearby pixels\n            kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n            motion = cv2.dilate(motion, kernel, iterations=2)\n            motion_mask = motion\n        self._prev_gray = gray.copy()\n\n        # Combine MOG2 and motion detection\n        combined = cv2.bitwise_or(mog_mask, motion_mask)\n\n        # Clean up\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return combined"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":593,"cacheRead":111746,"cacheWrite":1263,"totalTokens":113678,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795361053,"responseId":"0636f1e23fcff32d24bc28ca8dcfe243"}}
