ombined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n+174         combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n+175         return combined\n 158 \n 159     def _detect_skin(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n 160         \"\"\"Detect skin-colored pixels in YCrCb + HSV space.\"\"\"\n 161         h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n     ...","firstChangedLine":151},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795370016}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a2541ef","parentId":"07c84920","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:16:22.144Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also tune the detect_from_frame to be more lenient with the foreground mask (reduce the threshold). Let me also fix the aspect ratio constraint which might be too strict.\n\nAlso, the issue with 0 detections on the frame with 100% foreground pixels is strange. Let me check if the skin detection is the bottleneck.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that with 100% foreground pixels, the skin detection becomes critical. And since the skin detection uses YCrCb + HSV, it might be picking up a lot of the synthetic video's colors.\n\nLet me also make the skin detection more conservative - only detect very clear skin tones.\n\nActually wait - looking at the skin pixel count (505922), that's 39% of the frame! That's way too much. The skin detection is too loose.","thinkingSignature":"b2f3fd17d9015df6f2b40773eaf1523bb99e29a70b492fccdb9949be128c7988"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3nezmoz6acv1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, numpy as np, sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\n\n# Check skin detection on synthetic frame\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\nfor i in range(30): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\nycrcb = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YCrCb)\nhsv = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\nskin1 = cv2.inRange(ycrcb, np.array([0, 133, 77]), np.array([255, 173, 127]))\nskin2 = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 20, 70]), np.array([17, 255, 255]))\nskin = cv2.bitwise_or(skin1, skin2)\nkernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (7, 7))\nskin = cv2.dilate(skin, kernel, iterations=2)\n\n# Check contours\ncontours, _ = cv2.findContours(skin, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)\nprint(f\"Total skin contours: {len(contours)}\")\nbig = [(cv2.boundingRect(c), cv2.contourArea(c)) for c in contours if cv2.contourArea(c) > 500]\nbig.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\nfor (x,y,w,h), area in big[:10]:\n    aspect = h/max(w,1)\n    print(f\"  [{x},{y}] {w}x{h} area={area:.0f} aspect={aspect:.1f}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":603,"cacheRead":112443,"cacheWrite":1203,"totalTokens":114325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795370088,"responseId":"0636f1eb35635dafe0347cb9a03664bf"}}
