{"type":"message","id":"ffccf334","parentId":"7669a71b","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:16:41.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The first contour covers [0,0] to [1280,470] with area 453944 — that's the sky and background! The skin detection is way too loose on the synthetic video because the colors in the synthetic drawing are being picked up as skin.\n\nThe problem is that the synthetic video uses colors that overlap with skin tone ranges (the brown/tan ground, the skin-colored figures, etc.). The skin detector is picking up massive areas.\n\nI need a completely different approach for synthetic content. Instead of skin detection, I should:\n1. For the demo video (synthetic): use motion detection + shape detection\n\n\n2. For real video (webcam/upload): use skin + motion + shape\n\nBut the real issue is that this is a DEMO system. The user should use REAL video footage. The synthetic demo video is just for demonstration purposes.\n\nActually, looking at the contours again - there ARE person-like contours at [128,530] and [550,530] with proper aspect ratio (~1.3), but they're being drowned out by the massive false positive from the sky. The sky detection is generating false positives because the sky's blue is triggering the skin color ranges in HSV space.\n\nThe root cause is that the skin detector is too loose. The YCrCb range I'm using is standard, but the HSV range is catching the sky's blue. I need to tighten the skin detection constraints by requiring the skin region to have a minimum area and be positioned correctly, or switch to a more conservative approach that only marks skin when both YCrCb and HSV agree, with stricter thresholds and better shape filtering to ignore large uniform regions.","thinkingSignature":"49e0248907fb2becd8ad43e9bdfaeba8d89df799b0b357eba9752341193e5d7d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7b0qkpuvpzxv_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def _detect_skin(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Detect skin-colored pixels in YCrCb + HSV space.\"\"\"\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        ycrcb = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YCrCb)\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\n        # YCrCb skin ranges\n        skin1 = cv2.inRange(ycrcb, np.array([0, 133, 77]), np.array([255, 173, 127]))\n        # HSV skin ranges\n        skin2 = cv2.inRange(hsv, np.array([0, 20, 70]), np.array([17, 255, 255]))\n\n        skin = cv2.bitwise_or(skin1, skin2)\n\n        # Dilate to connect nearby skin pixels\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (7, 7))\n        skin = cv2.dilate(skin, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return skin","newText":"    def _detect_skin(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Detect skin-colored pixels — strict to avoid sky/background false positives.\"\"\"\n        ycrcb = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2YCrCb)\n\n        # YCrCb skin ranges (narrow to avoid background colors)\n        skin = cv2.inRange(ycrcb, np.array([0, 133, 80]), np.array([255, 173, 127]))\n\n        # Only keep skin regions with proper aspect ratio and size\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        skin = cv2.morphologyEx(skin, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n\n        # Find skin regions and filter by shape\n        contours, _ = cv2.findContours(skin, cv2.RETR_EXTERNAL, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        mask = np.zeros((h, w), dtype=np.uint8)\n        for cnt in contours:\n            area = cv2.contourArea(cnt)\n            if area < 200:  # too small\n                continue\n            x, y, cw, ch = cv2.boundingRect(cnt)\n            aspect = ch / max(cw, 1)\n            # Skin region should be roughly vertical (head) or reasonable body proportion\n            if aspect < 0.4:  # reject wide flat regions (sky, ground)\n                continue\n            if area > w * h * 0.3:  # reject huge regions\n                continue\n            cv2.drawContours(mask, [cnt], -1, 255, -1)\n\n        mask = cv2.dilate(mask, kernel, iterations=1)\n        return mask"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":255,"output":1086,"cacheRead":113048,"cacheWrite":1245,"totalTokens":115634,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795382988,"responseId":"0636f1f8e290a106b3508b114f037672"}}
