{"type":"message","id":"7ffb7f74","parentId":"a9a52396","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:17:21.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I also need to fix the `_prev_gray` initialization issue - it's an instance variable but I'm using it in the method. Let me check.\n\nAlso, the `_prev_gray` should be initialized per video/stream. Since this detector is reused, the `_prev_gray` should persist between frames in a video stream. Let me check if it's properly initialized.\n\nLooking at the code - `self._prev_gray = None` is set in `__init__`, and `_get_foreground` uses `self._prev_gray`. This should work.\n\nBut wait - the issue is that each call to `detect_from_frame` calls `_get_foreground`, which updates `self._prev_gray`. \n\nI'm realizing there's a state management problem here: the `PPEDetector` instance gets created fresh on each `/api/detect-frame` call in Flask, so `_prev_gray` resets every time. For the `VideoProcessor` though, which maintains a single instance, it should work correctly across frames. The real issue is that the background subtractor needs warm-up frames to build its model, and on the first few frames it'll be unreliable since it hasn't learned the background yet.\n\nFor Flask calls, I should initialize the background subtractor upfront rather than lazily, but actually skipping background subtraction for single-frame detection and relying on frame differencing makes more sense. Let me test the current implementation to see how it performs.","thinkingSignature":"90533afa5713f08ef9b59dac442d604fd15485a6f5a49c3ec5d41d356189f522"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n1dp8m24wz0w_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys, numpy as np\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\n\n# Warm up background model\nfor i in range(15):\n    ret, f = cap.read()\n    if ret:\n        _ = det._get_foreground(f)\n\n# Detect on frames 20-30\nresults = []\nfor i in range(15, 30):\n    ret, f = cap.read()\n    if not ret: break\n    dets = det.detect_from_frame(f)\n    results.append((i, len(dets), [d['ppe_status'] for d in dets]))\n\ncap.release()\n\nfor frame_num, n, statuses in results:\n    print(f\"Frame {frame_num}: {n} people  {[s.get('has_helmet') for s in statuses]}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":558,"cacheRead":114511,"cacheWrite":3398,"totalTokens":118543,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795429304,"responseId":"0636f22705a324d148119192f1b5fe85"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ba2ad3f","parentId":"7ffb7f74","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:17:24.071Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n1dp8m24wz0w_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Frame 15: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 16: 0 people  []\nFrame 17: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 18: 0 people  []\nFrame 19: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 20: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 21: 0 people  []\nFrame 22: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 23: 0 people  []\nFrame 24: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 25: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 26: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 27: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 28: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 29: 2 people  [True, True]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2379,"aggregated":"Frame 15: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 16: 0 people  []\nFrame 17: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 18: 0 people  []\nFrame 19: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 20: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 21: 0 people  []\nFrame 22: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 23: 0 people  []\nFrame 24: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 25: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 26: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 27: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 28: 1 people  [True]\nFrame 29: 2 people  [True, True]","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795444038}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbdfd222","parentId":"0ba2ad3f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:17:38.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The detector is finding only 1-2 people at a time, not all 4. This is because:\n1. The synthetic video workers are drawn as simple graphics that might not trigger consistent motion detection\n2. The background model is still not good enough for the synthetic videoThe issue is fundamental: the synthetic video has the workers standing almost still (just slight sinusoidal movement), and the MOG2 background subtractor with a static background model won't detect them well.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach for the demo: use frame differencing alone (without MOG2) and look for person-shaped regions. Since the workers are always visible, frame differencing will show movement (the slight motion).\n\n\nThe real problem is that the background subtraction approach struggles with static or near-static scenes. I should pivot to using skin detection paired with shape analysis as the primary method, treating motion detection as supplementary rather than foundational.","thinkingSignature":"c4dc609feda535c5e64ca5d75503249503c37a000be228ebb45cdef342d90c57"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6kt59bsvwb3b_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def _get_foreground(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get foreground mask using MOG2 + frame differencing.\"\"\"\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n        # MOG2 background subtraction\n        mog_mask = self._bg_subtractor.apply(frame, learningRate=0.02)\n\n        # Frame differencing (detect motion between consecutive frames)\n        motion_mask = np.zeros_like(gray)\n        if self._prev_gray is not None:\n            diff = cv2.absdiff(gray, self._prev_gray)\n            _, motion = cv2.threshold(diff, 12, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n            # Dilate motion to connect nearby pixels\n            kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n            motion = cv2.dilate(motion, kernel, iterations=2)\n            motion_mask = motion\n        self._prev_gray = gray.copy()\n\n        # Combine MOG2 and motion detection\n        combined = cv2.bitwise_or(mog_mask, motion_mask)\n\n        # Clean up\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return combined","newText":"    def _get_foreground(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n        \"\"\"Get foreground using MOG2 + frame differencing (whichever works better).\"\"\"\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n        # MOG2\n        mog_mask = self._bg_subtractor.apply(frame, learningRate=0.01)\n        _, mog_binary = cv2.threshold(mog_mask, 20, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n\n        # Frame differencing\n        motion_mask = np.zeros_like(gray)\n        if self._prev_gray is not None:\n            diff = cv2.absdiff(gray, self._prev_gray)\n            _, motion = cv2.threshold(diff, 10, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n            kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n            motion = cv2.dilate(motion, kernel, iterations=2)\n            motion_mask = motion\n        self._prev_gray = gray.copy()\n\n        # Use whichever gives reasonable foreground coverage\n        mog_pct = cv2.countNonZero(mog_binary) / max(gray.size, 1)\n        mot_pct = cv2.countNonZero(motion_mask) / max(gray.size, 1)\n\n        # If MOG2 thinks >60% is foreground, it's broken (new scene) — use motion instead\n        if mog_pct > 0.6:\n            combined = motion_mask\n        else:\n            combined = cv2.bitwise_or(mog_binary, motion_mask)\n\n        kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (5, 5))\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel, iterations=1)\n        combined = cv2.morphologyEx(combined, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel, iterations=2)\n        return combined"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":206,"output":1057,"cacheRead":115641,"cacheWrite":2870,"totalTokens":119774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795444105,"responseId":"0636f235d332f240c9799fc46e84a508"}}
