{"type":"message","id":"e8651056","parentId":"0a60ead1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:02.465Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iqd0j64k40jv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        rgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n        detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)\n        summary = self.detector.get_summary(detections)\n        violations = self.detector.get_violations(detections)\n\n        # Annotate frame\n        annotated = self._annotate_frame(frame.copy(), detections)\n\n        return annotated, detections, summary, violations\n\n    def _process_loop(self):\n        \"\"\"Background processing loop.\"\"\"\n        if self.use_webcam:\n            cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)\n        elif self.video_path:\n            cap = cv2.VideoCapture(self.video_path)\n        else:\n            return\n\n        if not cap.isOpened():\n            print(f\"[ERROR] Cannot open video source: {self.video_path}\")\n            return\n\n        frame_interval = max(1, int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS) / self.fps_target))\n        fps_delay = 1.0 / self.fps_target\n\n        print(f\"[VideoProcessor] Started — source: {'webcam' if self.use_webcam else self.video_path}\")\n        print(f\"[VideoProcessor] Processing 1 in every {frame_interval} frames (target {self.fps_target} fps)\")\n\n        while self._running:\n            ret, frame = cap.read()\n            if not ret:\n                # Loop video\n                if not self.use_webcam and self.video_path:\n                    cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES, 0)\n                    continue\n                break\n\n            self._frame_count += 1\n\n            # Skip frames for performance\n            if self._frame_count % frame_interval != 0:\n                continue\n\n            try:\n                annotated, detections, summary, violations = self.process_single_frame(frame)\n\n                with self._lock:\n                    self._last_results = detections\n                    self._last_summary = summary\n\n[62 more lines in file. Use offset=120 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795662447}}
{"type":"message","id":"be52094f","parentId":"e8651056","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:07.145Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue! The `_last_annotated_frame` is never set in `_process_loop`. Let me check if it's set somewhere.","thinkingSignature":"51bcbc3ed101267784be4c837c3fe2ec15c91c04e76d86dee81c4c03cbb21658"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o3aretz958ov_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","offset":120,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":453,"output":92,"cacheRead":118887,"cacheWrite":434,"totalTokens":119866,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795662477,"responseId":"0636f3103f719d49eb266cca5ebdc24d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"338a544d","parentId":"be52094f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:07.207Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o3aretz958ov_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                    self._last_annotated_frame = annotated.copy()\n\n                # Trigger callbacks\n                if self.on_detection:\n                    self.on_detection(frame, detections, summary)\n\n                if self.on_violation and violations:\n                    self.on_violation(violations, summary)\n\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"[ERROR] Frame processing failed: {e}\")\n\n            time.sleep(fps_delay)\n\n        cap.release()\n        self._running = False\n        print(\"[VideoProcessor] Stopped\")\n\n    def _annotate_frame(self, frame, detections):\n        \"\"\"Draw bounding boxes and labels on frame.\"\"\"\n        for det in detections:\n            x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in det[\"bbox\"]]\n            ppe = det[\"ppe_status\"]\n\n            if ppe[\"compliant\"]:\n                color = (0, 200, 0)   # Green\n                label = \"OK\"\n            else:\n                color = (0, 0, 220)   # Red\n                labels = []\n                if not ppe[\"has_helmet\"]:\n                    labels.append(\"NO HELMET\")\n                if not ppe[\"has_vest\"]:\n                    labels.append(\"NO VEST\")\n                label = \" | \".join(labels) if labels else \"VIOLATION\"\n\n            # Draw box\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), color, 2)\n\n            # Draw label\n\n[22 more lines in file. Use offset=160 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795667173}}
{"type":"message","id":"45cc8741","parentId":"338a544d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:12.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - `self._last_annotated_frame = annotated.copy()` is set at line 120. So the frame is stored. The `/api/frame` endpoint should work. But the issue might be that:\n\n1. The upload starts a NEW VideoProcessor which needs to warm up MOG2 with ~20-40 frames before detecting people\n2. The FPS is too slow for immediate feedback\n\nLet me test the `/api/frame` endpoint to see if it returns data.","thinkingSignature":"0c389c84c3fba13f38b78a9953102243cf11bad825cdd5fa6db85c1880c60029"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dklusnrmljnb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:5000/api/frame | wc -c\necho \"---\"\ncurl -s http://localhost:5000/api/summary | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d)\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":367,"output":187,"cacheRead":119219,"cacheWrite":615,"totalTokens":120388,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795667235,"responseId":"0636f314cbfecd67220a5599cd039c57"}}
