{"type":"message","id":"122b159d","parentId":"b7c03f02","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:22.696Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `/api/frame` endpoint returns data (933KB), and the backend is processing. The frame count is 1006 which means it's processing the video. But `total_persons: 0` means no people detected.\n\nThe issue is clear now:1. The processor has been running for 1006 frames and still 0 detections → the algorithm is too strict\n2. The MOG2 warmup is NOT the issue here - 1006 frames is way more than enough\n\nThe problem is the DETECTOR itself is too strict. The video frame differencing is probably not detecting people well because:1. \n\nThe detector is applying multiple filtering layers - frame differencing, aspect ratio checks, solidity thresholds, skin detection - and the combination is too aggressive. Even though my earlier test showed 2 people detected in demo video frames, the MOG2 background subtractor in the running backend might be producing a broken mask on this particular video. I should test the detector directly on the uploaded video file to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"c887c8fd7aec3250903f8ac006b30800d3398d60d03178e6b0250bd93b693e56"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4uujhlqk6oyd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what uploaded video exists\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_* 2>/dev/null || echo \"No uploaded files\"\necho \"---\"\n# Check current backend processing state\ntail -10 /tmp/s1-backend.log","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":136,"output":311,"cacheRead":119737,"cacheWrite":619,"totalTokens":120803,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795673513,"responseId":"0636f31bd8deca2c051d88f76ba9973a"}}
