{"type":"message","id":"b098b002","parentId":"2d510c6e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:34.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The uploaded video is **3840x2160 (4K UHD)** at 24fps! That's a massive resolution. The current detector processes at 2 FPS but on 4K frames, which is VERY slow. The MOG2 background subtractor on a 4K frame is extremely resource-intensive.\n\nAlso, the `min_body_height=80` at 4K means people need to be at least 80 pixels tall, which is fine for 4K. But the motion detection on 4K frames is very different from 720p.\n\nKey problems:\n1. **4K video (3840x2160)** — too large for real-time CPU processing\n\n\n2. **No downscaling** before processing\n3. **FPS target of 2** — at 4K this is barely achievable\n\nI need to downscale uploaded videos to 720p-1080p before processing them. I should also reduce the FPS target for uploaded videos since they typically have already been recorded, and prioritize detection quality over speed.\n\nLet me add downscaling to the VideoProcessor to handle high-resolution uploads efficiently.","thinkingSignature":"c7807530f0ef321e57ae7168a765ebe1cf33938807174cc7090e3c180898486b"},{"type":"text","text":"Video upload là **4K UHD (3840x2160)** — quá lớn để xử lý real-time. Cần resize trước khi detect:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cinodwielang_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check video properties\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2\nfor f in [\n    '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4'\n]:\n    cap = cv2.VideoCapture(f)\n    w = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))\n    h = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))\n    fps = cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS)\n    frames = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_COUNT))\n    cap.release()\n    print(f\"{w}x{h} @ {fps:.1f}fps, {frames} frames, 4K: {w>=3840}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":564,"output":477,"cacheRead":120164,"cacheWrite":607,"totalTokens":121812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795682835,"responseId":"0636f324465bf3d245d737c7ec00d0fa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e375525f","parentId":"b098b002","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:35.828Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cinodwielang_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3840x2160 @ 24.0fps, 391 frames, 4K: True"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":863,"aggregated":"3840x2160 @ 24.0fps, 391 frames, 4K: True","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795695803}}
{"type":"message","id":"80fe0223","parentId":"e375525f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:42.632Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so it's a 4K video with 24fps. The current FPS target is 2, and with 4K frames, this is very slow. The processor needs to process at 2fps but the processing itself takes long.\n\nKey fixes needed:\n1. **Downscale to 720p** before processing (both for MOG2 and detection)\n2. The aspect ratios and size thresholds need to be adjusted for the downscaled resolution\n\nLet me modify the VideoProcessor to resize frames to 720p before processing. This will speed up MOG2 dramatically.","thinkingSignature":"87a004ff8504575d7ddcc8cccf930c35c7ac6e54df990dfba7ef02a51f0d9079"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1di360ndar0l_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":69,"output":171,"cacheRead":120455,"cacheWrite":1325,"totalTokens":122020,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795695844,"responseId":"0636f33135b492d6bb73a9730eb6c9c1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8549249a","parentId":"80fe0223","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:42.726Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1di360ndar0l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nVideo Processor — Reads video file frame by frame and emits detections.\nCan also use webcam for live input.\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport time\nimport threading\nfrom collections import deque\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\n\nclass VideoProcessor:\n    \"\"\"\n    Processes video files (or webcam) and yields detection results per frame.\n    Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n        self.video_path = video_path\n        self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n        self.fps_target = fps_target  # Process every Nth frame for performance\n        self.detector = PPEDetector()\n        self._running = False\n        self._thread = None\n        self._frame_count = 0\n        self._last_results = []\n        self._last_summary = {}\n        self._last_annotated_frame = None\n        self._lock = threading.Lock()\n        # Callbacks\n        self.on_detection = None  # Called with (frame_rgb, detections, summary)\n        self.on_violation = None   # Called when violation detected\n\n    def start(self, on_detection=None, on_violation=None):\n        \"\"\"Start processing in a background thread.\"\"\"\n        self.on_detection = on_detection\n        self.on_violation = on_violation\n        self._running = True\n        self._thread = threading.Thread(target=self._process_loop, daemon=True)\n\n[141 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795702693}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4606330","parentId":"8549249a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:48.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to modify the VideoProcessor to:\n1. Auto-detect video resolution\n2. Downscale 4K videos to 720p for processing\n3. Keep the display/annotated frame at original resolution or a reasonable size\n\nLet me modify the `_process_loop` to resize frames for processing while keeping track of the scale factor.","thinkingSignature":"c5bcd506764b1bc31ff1a0455df602e12ec7819db8d9a1b108f32187a5be17a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tj8wyk16ieyv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","offset":100,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":380,"output":133,"cacheRead":121298,"cacheWrite":690,"totalTokens":122501,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795702758,"responseId":"0636f3384c14a541f5c86d840f70ac26"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0aaf2934","parentId":"b4606330","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:48.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tj8wyk16ieyv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            ret, frame = cap.read()\n            if not ret:\n                # Loop video\n                if not self.use_webcam and self.video_path:\n                    cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES, 0)\n                    continue\n                break\n\n            self._frame_count += 1\n\n            # Skip frames for performance\n            if self._frame_count % frame_interval != 0:\n                continue\n\n            try:\n                annotated, detections, summary, violations = self.process_single_frame(frame)\n\n                with self._lock:\n                    self._last_results = detections\n                    self._last_summary = summary\n                    self._last_annotated_frame = annotated.copy()\n\n                # Trigger callbacks\n                if self.on_detection:\n                    self.on_detection(frame, detections, summary)\n\n                if self.on_violation and violations:\n                    self.on_violation(violations, summary)\n\n            except Exception as e:\n\n[52 more lines in file. Use offset=130 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795708502}}
{"type":"message","id":"0188ff64","parentId":"0aaf2934","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:56.154Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add downscaling logic. The idea:1. Read frame at original resolution2. Resize to max 720p for processing3. Run detection on 720p frame4. Scale bbox coordinates back to original resolution5. Draw boxes on original-resolution annotated frame\n\nBut the `process_single_frame` and `detector.detect_from_frame` will receive the 720p frame. The bbox coordinates will be in 720p space. I need to store the scale factor and apply it when returning detections.Actually, the simplest approach: modify `process_single_frame` to accept a `scale` parameter and scale the bbox back.\n\n\nI'm going to restructure this with a preprocessing step that resizes high-resolution frames to 720p before passing them to detection, then scales the bounding boxes back to the original resolution after.","thinkingSignature":"261393172864aea766aed820e3c0d75b7a0d49491afee9e325d756b7b3f1ddee"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dnuq23l5nfn7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","offset":60,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":246,"output":232,"cacheRead":121812,"cacheWrite":657,"totalTokens":122947,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795708528,"responseId":"0636f33ec0ef0a546a5cfc299391e2f6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7529898b","parentId":"0188ff64","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:21:56.280Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dnuq23l5nfn7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                \"detections\": list(self._last_results),\n                \"summary\": dict(self._last_summary),\n                \"frame_count\": self._frame_count,\n            }\n\n    def process_single_frame(self, frame):\n        \"\"\"\n        Process a single frame directly (for API use).\n        Returns (annotated_frame, detections, summary)\n        \"\"\"\n        rgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n        detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)\n        summary = self.detector.get_summary(detections)\n        violations = self.detector.get_violations(detections)\n\n        # Annotate frame\n        annotated = self._annotate_frame(frame.copy(), detections)\n\n        return annotated, detections, summary, violations\n\n    def _process_loop(self):\n        \"\"\"Background processing loop.\"\"\"\n        if self.use_webcam:\n            cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)\n        elif self.video_path:\n            cap = cv2.VideoCapture(self.video_path)\n        else:\n            return\n\n        if not cap.isOpened():\n            print(f\"[ERROR] Cannot open video source: {self.video_path}\")\n            return\n\n        frame_interval = max(1, int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS) / self.fps_target))\n        fps_delay = 1.0 / self.fps_target\n\n        print(f\"[VideoProcessor] Started — source: {'webcam' if self.use_webcam else self.video_path}\")\n        print(f\"[VideoProcessor] Processing 1 in every {frame_interval} frames (target {self.fps_target} fps)\")\n\n        while self._running:\n            ret, frame = cap.read()\n            if not ret:\n                # Loop video\n                if not self.use_webcam and self.video_path:\n                    cap.set(cv2.CAP_PROP_POS_FRAMES, 0)\n                    continue\n                break\n\n            self._frame_count += 1\n\n\n[72 more lines in file. Use offset=110 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795716243}}
{"type":"message","id":"01019028","parentId":"7529898b","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:22:07.617Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me modify the VideoProcessor to:1. Detect 4K video and resize to 720p for processing\n2. Scale bbox back to original resolution\n3. Store original frame for annotation (resized to max 1080p)Let me rewrite the relevant parts.","thinkingSignature":"d85b7320d2bd94db6f231fc9d0ad919692795214cf0939e1bb7f845c328403d2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fvxfghrlzivi_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"class VideoProcessor:\n    \"\"\"\n    Processes video files (or webcam) and yields detection results per frame.\n    Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n        self.video_path = video_path\n        self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n        self.fps_target = fps_target  # Process every Nth frame for performance\n        self.detector = PPEDetector()\n        self._running = False\n        self._thread = None\n        self._frame_count = 0\n        self._last_results = []\n        self._last_summary = {}\n        self._last_annotated_frame = None\n        self._lock = threading.Lock()\n        # Callbacks\n        self.on_detection = None  # Called with (frame_rgb, detections, summary)\n        self.on_violation = None   # Called when violation detected","newText":"class VideoProcessor:\n    \"\"\"\n    Processes video files (or webcam) and yields detection results per frame.\n    Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n    Auto-downscales 4K video to 720p for CPU performance.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 1280   # Max width for detection processing\n\n    def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n        self.video_path = video_path\n        self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n        self.fps_target = fps_target\n        self.detector = PPEDetector()\n        self._running = False\n        self._thread = None\n        self._frame_count = 0\n        self._last_results = []\n        self._last_summary = {}\n        self._last_annotated_frame = None\n        self._lock = threading.Lock()\n        self._proc_scale = 1.0  # Scale factor for bbox coordinates\n        self._orig_size = None  # Original frame size for display\n        # Callbacks\n        self.on_detection = None\n        self.on_violation = None"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":457,"output":612,"cacheRead":122331,"cacheWrite":584,"totalTokens":123984,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795716310,"responseId":"0636f3469f8fb56a3f7e6aa3c8f3e389"}}
