{"type":"message","id":"7c7db93c","parentId":"a41ec97e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:24:03.436Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also, I need to reset the MOG2 background subtractor when resolution changes. Let me also handle that case. Actually, the MOG2 background subtractor might also have issues when resolution changes. Let me add a method to reset it.Actually, OpenCV's MOG2 can handle resolution changes but it needs to be reset. Let me add that.\n\nAlso, the key problem: the uploaded video has very different characteristics from the demo video. Let me test the detector on a frame from the actual uploaded video to understand what we're dealing with.","thinkingSignature":"a531bc3ff003bc120a837851043f8d380035a3dbe8bcd2388fb6ae9a36f04caa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gyqhxsg0yxzp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys, numpy as np\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\n# Read frame from uploaded 4K video\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4')\nfor i in range(50): cap.read()  # skip to frame 50\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\nif ret:\n    print(f\"Frame: {frame.shape}\")\n    \n    # Downscale to 720p for processing\n    proc = cv2.resize(frame, (1280, 720))\n    \n    # Warm up MOG2 with 20 frames\n    print(\"Warming up...\")\n    for i in range(20):\n        _ = det._get_foreground(proc)\n    \n    # Detect\n    dets = det.detect_from_frame(proc)\n    print(f\"Detections: {len(dets)}\")\n    for d in dets:\n        x1,y1,x2,y2 = d['bbox']\n        print(f\"  [{x1:.0f},{y1:.0f}]-[{x2:.0f},{y2:.0f}] \"\n              f\"conf={d['confidence']:.2f} \"\n              f\"H={d['ppe_status']['has_helmet']} V={d['ppe_status']['has_vest']}\")\n    \n    # Check foreground\n    fg = det._get_foreground(proc)\n    fg_pct = cv2.countNonZero(fg) / (720*1280) * 100\n    print(f\"Foreground: {fg_pct:.1f}%\")\n    \n    sm = det.get_summary(dets)\n    print(f\"Summary: {sm}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":574,"cacheRead":126986,"cacheWrite":1453,"totalTokens":129089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795831888,"responseId":"0636f3b951950d37b5692876197ebf31"}}
{"type":"message","id":"adce93fb","parentId":"7c7db93c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:24:10.007Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gyqhxsg0yxzp_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Frame: (2160, 3840, 3)\nWarming up...\nDetections: 0\nForeground: 0.0%\nSummary: {'total_persons': 0, 'compliant': 0, 'violations': 0, 'no_helmet': 0, 'no_vest': 0, 'compliance_rate': 100.0}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6494,"aggregated":"Frame: (2160, 3840, 3)\nWarming up...\nDetections: 0\nForeground: 0.0%\nSummary: {'total_persons': 0, 'compliant': 0, 'violations': 0, 'no_helmet': 0, 'no_vest': 0, 'compliance_rate': 100.0}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795849988}}
{"type":"message","id":"46e6a4e6","parentId":"adce93fb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:24:20.280Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The foreground is 0% which means MOG2 thinks the entire frame is background. This is because:1. The warmup with 20 frames might not be enough for MOG2 to learn the background\n2. The motion in the video might be minimal compared to the background\n3. The people might be very small in the 4K frame (scaled to 720p)Let me check what the frame looks like and what the skin detection sees.","thinkingSignature":"f83e293d6f39b4f9425a7249792a0648698a101fc3d848f2f660ef9cbf1bb333"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_myozwaklljj1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys, numpy as np\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4')\nfor i in range(50): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\nproc = cv2.resize(frame, (1280, 720))\nprint(f\"Proc shape: {proc.shape}\")\n\n# Check skin detection\nskin = det._detect_skin(proc)\nskin_pixels = cv2.countNonZero(skin)\nprint(f\"Skin pixels: {skin_pixels} ({skin_pixels/(720*1280)*100:.2f}%)\")\n\n# Save sample frame for analysis\ncv2.imwrite('/tmp/frame_50_720p.jpg', proc)\nprint(\"Saved /tmp/frame_50_720p.jpg\")\n\n# Check edges\ngray = cv2.cvtColor(proc, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\nedges = cv2.Canny(gray, 50, 150)\nedge_pct = cv2.countNonZero(edges) / (720*1280) * 100\nprint(f\"Edge pixels: {edge_pct:.1f}%\")\n\n# Try with more MOG2 warmup\nprint(\"\\nWith 50-frame warmup:\")\nfor i in range(50):\n    _ = det._get_foreground(proc)\nfg = det._get_foreground(proc)\nfg_pct = cv2.countNonZero(fg) / (720*1280) * 100\nprint(f\"Fg pixels after warmup: {fg_pct:.2f}%\")\nPYEOF","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":127,"output":544,"cacheRead":127321,"cacheWrite":1736,"totalTokens":129728,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795850026,"responseId":"0636f3cb4c378f11bab2aa14a9d6ce10"}}
