{"type":"message","id":"38c31ae5","parentId":"df6625a6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:24:50.927Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the actual uploaded video. The issue is that the uploaded video is a real construction site video and the people might be very small, stationary, or the video might be quite different from what our algorithm expects.\n\nLet me think about a different approach. The current algorithm relies heavily on MOG2 foreground detection. But if the people are stationary (no motion), MOG2 won't detect them. The skin detection is too weak (only 0.08%).\n\nLet me try a different approach for real videos: **HOG (Histogram of Oriented Gradients)** or **Upper-body detection** using a pre-trained Haar cascade.\n \nSince we're limited by what OpenCV provides, I'll focus on enhancing the existing detector by implementing a fallback mechanism that activates skin detection when motion is absent, and significantly boosting skin detection sensitivity to catch people even when they're standing still.","thinkingSignature":"f98c6ba4bc47b1b3d40e9ff4aa183d33517f566f6be380ff8f623cb71f33db09"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pb8tt7sl6kyb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if we have any pre-trained cascades\nfind /usr /opt /usr/local -name \"*.xml\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"body\\|person\\|haar\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"---\"\npython3 -c \"\nimport cv2\nfor f in cv2.data.haarcascades.split():\n    print(f)\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"No data.haarcascades\"\npython3 -c \"import cv2; print(cv2.data.haarcascades)\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":49,"output":328,"cacheRead":129768,"cacheWrite":340,"totalTokens":130485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795881045,"responseId":"0636f3ea37b9ddd442ab41c7c8ee545d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a6bb69c","parentId":"38c31ae5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:24:58.459Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pb8tt7sl6kyb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_smile.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_license_plate_rus_16stages.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_lowerbody.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_fullbody.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_upperbody.xml\n\nCommand timed out after 5 seconds. If this command is expected to take longer, re-run with a higher timeout (e.g., exec timeout=300). If it should keep running, start it with exec background=true or yieldMs so OpenClaw can register a pollable process session. Do not rely on shell backgrounding with a trailing &."}],"details":{"status":"failed","exitCode":null,"durationMs":7478,"aggregated":"/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_smile.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_license_plate_rus_16stages.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_lowerbody.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_fullbody.xml\n/usr/local/lib/python3.10/dist-packages/cv2/data/haarcascade_upperbody.xml","timedOut":true,"cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795898435}}
{"type":"message","id":"cdf6defa","parentId":"6a6bb69c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:25:06.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have OpenCV's built-in Haar cascades for:- `haarcascade_fullbody.xml`\n- `haarcascade_upperbody.xml`\n- `haarcascade_lowerbody.xml`\n- `haarcascade_smile.xml`\n- `haarcascade_license_plate_rus_16stages.xml`These are pre-trained classifiers for body detection. They're not as good as YOLO but they work without internet! Let me use the upperbody cascade for detecting people, combined with our PPE color analysis.","thinkingSignature":"ce5081ff22df99171f64e2a016be6bbaea11ae6d703e2407e54e4d5ebed98393"},{"type":"text","text":"Có sẵn Haar cascades! Dùng `upperbody` + `fullbody` cascade để detect người — không cần internet:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zt7jofu9dv72_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"\"\"\"","newText":"\"\"\"\nS1 PPE Detection Engine v3 — Haar Cascade + Skin + Color Analysis\nUses OpenCV pre-trained cascades (no internet required)\n\"\"\""}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":225,"output":239,"cacheRead":129990,"cacheWrite":463,"totalTokens":130917,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795898492,"responseId":"0636f3fcdd42ad6aba288216542535dc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c0775469","parentId":"cdf6defa","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:25:06.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zt7jofu9dv72_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"edit\",\n  \"error\": \"Found 18 occurrences of the text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py. The text must be unique. Please provide more context to make it unique.\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"edit","error":"Found 18 occurrences of the text in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py. The text must be unique. Please provide more context to make it unique."},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795906719}}
{"type":"message","id":"2701d38e","parentId":"c0775469","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:25:45.886Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me write a completely new detector that uses Haar cascades instead.","thinkingSignature":"604309eae424413d38d754b883dd13ad55ab669554c80e9bc8b9e99525dda70e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ot9q6nj718ui_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","content":"\"\"\"\nS1 PPE Detection Engine v3 — Haar Cascade + Skin + Color Analysis\nUses OpenCV pre-trained cascades for person detection.\nCombines cascade detection + PPE color analysis.\n\"\"\"\nimport cv2\nimport numpy as np\nfrom collections import deque\n\n\nclass PPEDetector:\n    \"\"\"\n    PPE detection using Haar cascades + color analysis.\n    Cascade-based detection works on stationary subjects (unlike MOG2).\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        min_body_height: int = 60,\n        min_body_width: int = 25,\n        conf_threshold: float = 0.4,\n    ):\n        self.conf_threshold = conf_threshold\n        self.min_body_height = min_body_height\n        self.min_body_width = min_body_width\n\n        # Load OpenCV Haar cascades\n        cascade_dir = cv2.data.haarcascades\n        self._upper_cascade = cv2.CascadeClassifier(\n            cascade_dir + 'haarcascade_upperbody.xml')\n        self._full_cascade = cv2.CascadeClassifier(\n            cascade_dir + 'haarcascade_fullbody.xml')\n\n        # State for smoothing\n        self._history = deque(maxlen=5)\n        self._prev_gray = None\n\n    def process_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray):\n        detections = self.detect_from_frame(frame)\n        annotated = self._annotate(frame.copy(), detections)\n        return detections, annotated\n\n    def _annotate(self, frame, detections):\n        for d in detections:\n            x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in d['bbox']]\n            ppe = d['ppe_status']\n            ok = ppe.get('compliant', False)\n            col = (0, 200, 83) if ok else (255, 23, 68)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), col, 2)\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (col[0]//3, col[1]//3, col[2]//3), -1)\n            label = 'OK' if ok else (\n                'NO-HELMET' if not ppe.get('has_helmet') and not ppe.get('has_vest')\n                else 'NO-HELMET' if not ppe.get('has_helmet')\n                else 'NO-VEST'\n            )\n            lw = len(label) * 8 + 12\n            cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, max(0, y1 - 24)), (x1 + lw, y1), (0, 0, 0), -1)\n            cv2.putText(frame, label, (x1 + 6, y1 - 8),\n                cv2.FONT_HERSHEY_SIMPLEX, 0.48, col, 1)\n        return frame\n\n    def detect_from_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]:\n        h, w = frame.shape[:2]\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        if gray.dtype != np.uint8:\n            gray = gray.astype(np.uint8)\n\n        # ── Multi-scale Haar cascade detection ───────────────────────────────\n        all_boxes = []\n\n        # Scale factors for multi-scale detection\n        scales = [1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6, 1.8, 2.0]\n\n        for scale in scales:\n            sw = int(w / scale)\n            sh = int(h / scale)\n            if sw < 100 or sh < 100:\n                continue\n            gray_small = cv2.resize(gray, (sw, sh))\n\n            # Upper body cascade\n            uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n                minSize=(30, 30), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n                all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n                                   int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))\n\n            # Full body cascade\n            fulls = self._full_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n                minSize=(30, 60), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (fx, fy, fw, fh) in fulls:\n                all_boxes.append((int(fx * scale), int(fy * scale),\n                                   int(fw * scale), int(fh * scale), 'full'))\n\n        if not all_boxes:\n            return []\n\n        # ── Merge overlapping boxes ────────────────────────────────────────\n        merged = self._merge_boxes(all_boxes, w, h)\n        if not merged:\n            return []\n\n        # ── Analyze each candidate for PPE ────────────────────────────────\n        detections = []\n        for (bx1, by1, bw, bh) in merged:\n            bx2, by2 = bx1 + bw, by1 + bh\n\n            # Skip if too small\n            if bh < self.min_body_height or bw < self.min_body_width:\n                continue\n            # Skip if touching edges of frame\n            if bx1 < 5 or by1 < 5:\n                continue\n\n            ppe = self._analyze_ppe(frame, bx1, by1, bx2, by2, bw, bh)\n\n            conf = min(0.45 + (bh / h) * 0.3, 0.88)\n\n            detections.append({\n                \"bbox\": [float(bx1), float(by1), float(bx2), float(by2)],\n                \"confidence\": round(conf, 3),\n                \"class_id\": 0,\n                \"class_name\": \"person\",\n                \"ppe_status\": {\n                    \"has_helmet\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"],\n                    \"has_vest\": ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                    \"compliant\": ppe[\"has_helmet\"] and ppe[\"has_vest\"],\n                },\n                \"width\": float(bw),\n                \"height\": float(bh),\n                \"center_x\": float(bx1 + bw / 2),\n                \"center_y\": float(by1 + bh / 2),\n            })\n\n        # NMS\n        detections = self._nms(detections)\n        return detections\n\n    def _merge_boxes(self, boxes: list, frame_w: int, frame_h: int) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Merge boxes at same location from multiple scales/cascades.\"\"\"\n        if not boxes:\n            return []\n        # Group by approximate position\n        merged = {}\n        for (x, y, w, h, box_type) in boxes:\n            # Normalize to a grid\n            gx = x // 50\n            gy = y // 50\n            key = (gx, gy)\n            if key not in merged:\n                merged[key] = (x, y, w, h)\n            else:\n                # Keep larger box\n                _, _, ew, eh = merged[key]\n                if w * h > ew * eh:\n                    merged[key] = (x, y, w, h)\n\n        # Expand boxes slightly and clamp to frame\n        result = []\n        for (x, y, w, h) in merged.values():\n            # Expand by 10%\n            ex = max(0, int(x - w * 0.05))\n            ey = max(0, int(y - h * 0.05))\n            ew = min(frame_w, int(w * 1.1))\n            eh = min(frame_h, int(h * 1.1))\n            result.append((ex, ey, ew, eh))\n        return result\n\n    def _nms(self, detections: list, iou_thresh: float = 0.4) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Non-Maximum Suppression.\"\"\"\n        if not detections:\n            return []\n        boxes = [(d['bbox'][0], d['bbox'][1],\n                  d['bbox'][2]-d['bbox'][0], d['bbox'][3]-d['bbox'][1])\n                 for d in detections]\n        scores = [d['confidence'] for d in detections]\n        indices = self._hard_nms(boxes, scores, iou_thresh)\n        return [detections[i] for i in indices]\n\n    def _hard_nms(self, boxes, scores, thresh):\n        boxes = np.array(boxes, dtype=float)\n        scores = np.array(scores, dtype=float)\n        x1, y1 = boxes[:, 0], boxes[:, 1]\n        x2, y2 = boxes[:, 0] + boxes[:, 2], boxes[:, 1] + boxes[:, 3]\n        areas = boxes[:, 2] * boxes[:, 3]\n        order = scores.argsort()[::-1]\n        keep = []\n        while order.size > 0:\n            i = order[0]\n            keep.append(i)\n            if order.size == 1:\n                break\n            xx1 = np.maximum(x1[i], x1[order[1:]])\n            yy1 = np.maximum(y1[i], y1[order[1:]])\n            xx2 = np.minimum(x2[i], x2[order[1:]])\n            yy2 = np.minimum(y2[i], y2[order[1:]])\n            inter = np.maximum(0, xx2 - xx1) * np.maximum(0, yy2 - yy1)\n            union = areas[i] + areas[order[1:]] - inter\n            iou = inter / np.maximum(union, 1e-6)\n            order = order[1:][iou <= thresh]\n        return keep\n\n    def _analyze_ppe(\n        self, frame: np.ndarray,\n        bx1: int, by1: int, bx2: int, by2: int,\n        bw: int, bh: int\n    ) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Analyze helmet and vest in detected region.\"\"\"\n        fh, fw = frame.shape[:2]\n        bx1, by1 = max(0, bx1), max(0, by1)\n        bx2, by2 = min(fw, bx2), min(fh, by2)\n        body = frame[by1:by2, bx1:bx2]\n        if body.size == 0:\n            return {\"has_helmet\": True, \"has_vest\": True}\n\n        hsv = cv2.cvtColor(body, cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)\n\n        has_helmet = False\n        has_vest = False\n\n        # HELMET: top 25% of bounding box\n        helmet_end = int(bh * 0.25)\n        if helmet_end > 5:\n            helmet_hsv = hsv[:helmet_end, :]\n            has_helmet = self._check_helmet(helmet_hsv)\n\n        # VEST: middle 25-70% of bounding box\n        vest_top = int(bh * 0.25)\n        vest_bot = int(bh * 0.70)\n        if vest_bot > vest_top:\n            vest_hsv = hsv[vest_top:vest_bot, :]\n            has_vest = self._check_vest(vest_hsv)\n\n        return {\"has_helmet\": has_helmet, \"has_vest\": has_vest}\n\n    def _check_helmet(self, hsv_roi: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        if hsv_roi.size == 0:\n            return False\n        h_roi, w_roi = hsv_roi.shape[:2]\n        if h_roi < 5 or w_roi < 5:\n            return False\n\n        # Multiple helmet colors\n        ranges = [\n            ([15, 30, 60], [40, 255, 255]),  # Yellow\n            ([0, 40, 60], [18, 255, 255]),    # Orange\n            ([0, 0, 160], [180, 30, 255]),    # White\n            ([90, 30, 50], [130, 255, 255]),  # Blue\n            ([0, 40, 50], [10, 255, 255]),    # Red\n        ]\n        mask = np.zeros(hsv_roi.shape[:2], dtype=np.uint8)\n        for lo, hi in ranges:\n            mask = cv2.bitwise_or(mask, cv2.inRange(hsv_roi, np.array(lo), np.array(hi)))\n\n        ratio = cv2.countNonZero(mask) / max(mask.size, 1)\n        return ratio > 0.08\n\n    def _check_vest(self, hsv_roi: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n        if hsv_roi.size == 0:\n            return False\n        h_roi, w_roi = hsv_roi.shape[:2]\n        if h_roi < 5 or w_roi < 5:\n            return False\n\n        # Orange/yellow vest\n        vest_mask = np.zeros(hsv_roi.shape[:2], dtype=np.uint8)\n        for lo, hi in [\n            ([0, 50, 80], [15, 255, 255]),\n            ([20, 40, 80], [45, 255, 255]),\n            ([45, 40, 80], [75, 255, 255]),\n        ]:\n            vest_mask = cv2.bitwise_or(vest_mask,\n                cv2.inRange(hsv_roi, np.array(lo), np.array(hi)))\n\n        vest_ratio = cv2.countNonZero(vest_mask) / max(vest_mask.size, 1)\n        if vest_ratio > 0.12:\n            return True\n\n        # Reflective stripes detection\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(hsv_roi, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        blur = cv2.GaussianBlur(gray, (7, 7), 0)\n        _, bright = cv2.threshold(blur, 200, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)\n        row_sums = bright.sum(axis=1) / 255\n        if len(row_sums) > 3:\n            transitions = np.abs(np.diff(np.sign(row_sums - w_roi * 0.3)))\n            if np.sum(transitions) >= 2:\n                return True\n\n        return False\n\n    def get_violations(self, detections):\n        return [d for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"compliant\"]]\n\n    def get_summary(self, detections):\n        total = len(detections)\n        compliant = sum(1 for d in detections if d[\"ppe_status\"][\"compliant\"])\n        violations = total - compliant\n        no_helmet = sum(1 for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"has_helmet\"])\n        no_vest = sum(1 for d in detections if not d[\"ppe_status\"][\"has_vest\"])\n        return {\n            \"total_persons\": total,\n            \"compliant\": compliant,\n            \"violations\": violations,\n            \"no_helmet\": no_helmet,\n            \"no_vest\": no_vest,\n            \"compliance_rate\": round(compliant / total * 100, 1) if total > 0 else 100.0,\n        }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    det = PPEDetector()\n    print(f\"PPEDetector v3 ready (Haar Cascade + Color)\")\n    print(\"Cascades:\", det._upper_cascade.empty(), det._full_cascade.empty())\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":111,"output":3427,"cacheRead":130120,"cacheWrite":765,"totalTokens":134423,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795906805,"responseId":"0636f4047782ed7b786ff9a522d4e26c"}}
