{"type":"message","id":"ae228acc","parentId":"0f5a008c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:26:18.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The Haar cascade detector found **3 people** in the 4K video frame (at 720p). But 4.55s per frame is too slow for real-time. I need to optimize the detection:\n\n1. The multi-scale detection loops through 6 scales - this is expensive\n2. Using both upperbody and fullbody cascades on 6 scales each = 12 detections per frame\n\nLet me optimize:\n1. Reduce number of scales (3-4 instead of 6)\n2. Use only upperbody cascade (more reliable for PPE)\n3. Or use fewer scales with larger steps\n\nAlso, 4.55s per frame at 1280x720 is quite slow. \n\nThe real bottleneck is running both cascades across multiple scales. I should pare this down to just the upperbody detector at 2-3 scales, since fullbody tends to be noisier anyway. The good news is that at 1280x720 with a 2 FPS target, I have 500ms per frame to work with, so even if this takes a few seconds, the queue should handle it. Let me reduce the scales to 3 and test whether that brings the processing time down to something manageable.","thinkingSignature":"9ce1a04881ca7229419c1646ec98dca92184c406064faae92934dc2617781d1f"},{"type":"text","text":"3 người detected! Nhưng 4.5s/frame — quá chậm. Tối ưu:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l28cll09kl1g_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"        # Scale factors for multi-scale detection\n        scales = [1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6, 1.8, 2.0]","newText":"        # Scale factors for multi-scale detection (3 scales = faster)\n        scales = [1.0, 1.5, 2.0]"},{"oldText":"            # Upper body cascade\n            uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n                minSize=(30, 30), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n                all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n                                   int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))\n\n            # Full body cascade\n            fulls = self._full_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n                minSize=(30, 60), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (fx, fy, fw, fh) in fulls:\n                all_boxes.append((int(fx * scale), int(fy * scale),\n                                   int(fw * scale), int(fh * scale), 'full'))","newText":"            # Upper body cascade (most reliable for PPE detection)\n            uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4,\n                minSize=(40, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n                all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n                                   int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":207,"output":762,"cacheRead":130959,"cacheWrite":3898,"totalTokens":135826,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776795964169,"responseId":"0636f43e1a3cf027cacee25f37c7691c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3ae3519","parentId":"ae228acc","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:26:18.702Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l28cll09kl1g_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  67 \n  68         # ── Multi-scale Haar cascade detection ───────────────────────────────\n  69         all_boxes = []\n  70 \n- 71         # Scale factors for multi-scale detection\n- 72         scales = [1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6, 1.8, 2.0]\n+ 71         # Scale factors for multi-scale detection (3 scales = faster)\n+ 72         scales = [1.0, 1.5, 2.0]\n  73 \n  74         for scale in scales:\n  75             sw = int(w / scale)\n  76             sh = int(h / scale)\n  77             if sw < 100 or sh < 100:\n  78                 continue\n  79             gray_small = cv2.resize(gray, (sw, sh))\n  80 \n- 81             # Upper body cascade\n+ 81             # Upper body cascade (most reliable for PPE detection)\n  82             uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n- 83                 gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n- 84                 minSize=(30, 30), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n+ 83                 gray_small, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4,\n+ 84                 minSize=(40, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n  85             for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n  86                 all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n  87                                    int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))\n  88 \n- 89             # Full body cascade\n- 90             fulls = self._full_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n- 91                 gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n- 92                 minSize=(30, 60), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n- 93             for (fx, fy, fw, fh) in fulls:\n- 94                 all_boxes.append((int(fx * scale), int(fy * scale),\n- 95                                    int(fw * scale), int(fh * scale), 'full'))\n- 96 \n  97         if not all_boxes:\n  98             return []\n  99 \n 100         # ── Merge overlapping boxes ────────────────────────────────────────\n     ...","firstChangedLine":71},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776795978670}}
