{"type":"message","id":"9408eedb","parentId":"afa74b8f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:26:55.930Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also, I need to update the VideoProcessor to use 640x360 for 4K videos (faster processing) and 960x540 for 1080p. Let me also update the MAX_PROC_WIDTH to 640 for faster detection.\n\nActually, for the uploaded video at 3840x2160, even at 1280p the detection takes 1 second. At 640p it should be much faster (roughly 0.25s). Let me try 640p.","thinkingSignature":"e1dc2755fb1f4d7b9323079bfa51961777fe4764cd39caa9e0fdbcdd05cdfc23"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1b3s9guhvv0n_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 1280   # Max width for detection processing","newText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 960    # Max width for detection (speed vs accuracy)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":76,"output":204,"cacheRead":136267,"cacheWrite":363,"totalTokens":136910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796009751,"responseId":"0636f46ba52aa26c7a192d14237b9fdb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"acabb7f7","parentId":"9408eedb","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:26:56.104Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1b3s9guhvv0n_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  16     Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n  17     Auto-downscales 4K video to 720p for CPU performance.\n  18     \"\"\"\n  19 \n- 20     MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 1280   # Max width for detection processing\n+ 20     MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 960    # Max width for detection (speed vs accuracy)\n  21 \n  22     def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n  23         self.video_path = video_path\n  24         self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n     ...","firstChangedLine":20},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796016019}}
{"type":"message","id":"91e4daef","parentId":"acabb7f7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:27:05.967Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also update the FPS for uploaded videos. The current FPS_TARGET=2 from env might be too slow for 4K video. Let me also increase it for uploaded videos. Actually, let me also check the FPS target. If it's 2 FPS and detection takes 1s, then there's only 1s for queue to fill up per detection. This should be fine actually.Let me test the speed now with 2 scales + 960p.","thinkingSignature":"f405ffb21639a6ddb79315591912d0bab85b2fdd8f1b7f826bb0fb81d3623b35"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4d6d6zjxzsjt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys, time\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4')\nfor i in range(50): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\n# Test at 640p, 960p, 1280p\nfor W in [640, 960, 1280]:\n    proc = cv2.resize(frame, (W, int(frame.shape[0] * W/frame.shape[1])))\n    start = time.time()\n    for _ in range(3):\n        dets = det.detect_from_frame(proc)\n    elapsed = (time.time() - start) / 3\n    print(f\"  {W}p: {elapsed:.2f}s/frame, {len(dets)} detections\")\nPYEOF","timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":75,"output":376,"cacheRead":136393,"cacheWrite":485,"totalTokens":137329,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796016138,"responseId":"0636f471dcaafff2e4d9cc11a266358c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"35c27f0f","parentId":"91e4daef","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:27:15.316Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4d6d6zjxzsjt_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"640p: 0.17s/frame, 0 detections\n  960p: 0.41s/frame, 0 detections\n  1280p: 0.75s/frame, 1 detections"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9285,"aggregated":"640p: 0.17s/frame, 0 detections\n  960p: 0.41s/frame, 0 detections\n  1280p: 0.75s/frame, 1 detections","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796035293}}
{"type":"message","id":"81ce8fb3","parentId":"35c27f0f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:27:27.824Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! At 640p and 960p, no detections. At 1280p, 1 detection. This means the people in the video are relatively small in the frame. At 1280p, we get 1 detection. At lower resolutions, the cascade can't detect them because they're too small relative to the search window.\n\nLet me try at 1280p with different scale factors. Maybe the people need a specific scale range.Also, maybe I need to add a fallback to fullbody cascade when upperbody doesn't find anything.Let me try a different approach: detect at multiple resolutions and combine results. Or use the fullbody cascade as a fallback.Actually, the issue might be that:1. \n\nThe upperbody cascade needs at least 40x40 pixel detection, which at 4K (3840x2160) means people occupy only about 2.5-4% of the frame height. After scaling down to 1280x720, they're roughly 72-108 pixels tall—detectable but challenging. At 960p they drop to 54-81 pixels, right at the minimum threshold. I should add the fullbody cascade as a fallback for these small detections.","thinkingSignature":"fac04399d2e8dac02b6d2059c321e804206127c46a5b0f0acc1b14014a2e85f2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wrvxjngwd8aq_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py","edits":[{"oldText":"            # Upper body cascade (most reliable for PPE detection)\n            uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4,\n                minSize=(40, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n                all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n                                   int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))","newText":"            # Upper body cascade\n            uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4,\n                minSize=(30, 30), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n                all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n                                   int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))\n\n            # Full body cascade as fallback\n            fulls = self._full_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n                gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n                minSize=(20, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n            for (fx, fy, fw, fh) in fulls:\n                all_boxes.append((int(fx * scale), int(fy * scale),\n                                   int(fw * scale), int(fh * scale), 'full'))"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":97,"output":644,"cacheRead":136669,"cacheWrite":628,"totalTokens":138038,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796035333,"responseId":"0636f4858be569e85ece3463a2296990"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bf74d12","parentId":"81ce8fb3","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:27:27.922Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wrvxjngwd8aq_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/detector.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  77             if sw < 100 or sh < 100:\n  78                 continue\n  79             gray_small = cv2.resize(gray, (sw, sh))\n  80 \n- 81             # Upper body cascade (most reliable for PPE detection)\n+ 81             # Upper body cascade\n  82             uppers = self._upper_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n  83                 gray_small, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4,\n- 84                 minSize=(40, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n+ 84                 minSize=(30, 30), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n  85             for (ux, uy, uw, uh) in uppers:\n  86                 all_boxes.append((int(ux * scale), int(uy * scale),\n  87                                    int(uw * scale), int(uh * scale), 'upper'))\n  88 \n+ 89             # Full body cascade as fallback\n+ 90             fulls = self._full_cascade.detectMultiScale(\n+ 91                 gray_small, scaleFactor=1.1, minNeighbors=3,\n+ 92                 minSize=(20, 40), maxSize=(sw, sh))\n+ 93             for (fx, fy, fw, fh) in fulls:\n+ 94                 all_boxes.append((int(fx * scale), int(fy * scale),\n+ 95                                    int(fw * scale), int(fh * scale), 'full'))\n+ 96 \n  89         if not all_boxes:\n  90             return []\n  91 \n  92         # ── Merge overlapping boxes ────────────────────────────────────────\n     ...","firstChangedLine":81},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796047886}}
