{"type":"message","id":"eed7438d","parentId":"1be4cbe0","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:28:02.570Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6686z4r0t43e_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"4K video @ 1280p: 4.66s, 1 people\n  [1166,334] 103x85 H=True V=True\n\nDemo video: 1.78s, 2 people\n  [515,442] 180x146 H=True V=False\n  [102,449] 162x132 H=True V=False\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"wild-fjord","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"4K video @ 1280p: 4.66s, 1 people\n  [1166,334] 103x85 H=True V=True\n\nDemo video: 1.78s, 2 people\n  [515,442] 180x146 H=True V=False\n  [102,449] 162x132 H=True V=False\n","name":"python3 <<"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796082550}}
{"type":"message","id":"947dab99","parentId":"eed7438d","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:28:13.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n1. 4K video @ 1280p: 4.66s, 1 person detected (but user says 3 people in video) — 1 person detected, accuracy is low\n2. Demo video: 1.78s, 2 people detected\n\nThe speed is still slow (1.78s for demo video, 4.66s for 4K at 1280p). This is because we have 4 scales x 2 cascades = 8 cascade detections per frame.\n\nThe main issues:\n1. **Too slow** — 1-5 seconds per frame is not real-time","thinkingSignature":"9149a327722d301fd148b7c038fff9b5deeb91116d85afeeb22d044e8b14f896"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1b1l080fokpc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2\n# Time individual cascade operations\nimport time\ncascade_dir = cv2.data.haarcascades\nuc = cv2.CascadeClassifier(cascade_dir + 'haarcascade_upperbody.xml')\nfc = cv2.CascadeClassifier(cascade_dir + 'haarcascade_fullbody.xml')\n\nimg = cv2.resize(cv2.imread('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/test_frame.jpg'), (1280, 720))\ngray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n# Time each scale\nfor scale in [0.8, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0]:\n    sw, sh = int(1280/scale), int(720/scale)\n    g = cv2.resize(gray, (sw, sh))\n    t = time.time()\n    r = uc.detectMultiScale(g, scaleFactor=1.15, minNeighbors=4, minSize=(30,30), maxSize=(sw,sh))\n    print(f'Upperbody scale={scale}: {time.time()-t:.2f}s -> {len(r)} found')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":132,"output":425,"cacheRead":138264,"cacheWrite":696,"totalTokens":139517,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796082590,"responseId":"0636f4b47bbd78d8dcbc4df1494704e8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d505f93c","parentId":"947dab99","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:28:16.342Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1b1l080fokpc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Upperbody scale=0.8: 1.14s -> 0 found\nUpperbody scale=1.0: 0.83s -> 1 found\nUpperbody scale=1.5: 0.39s -> 1 found\nUpperbody scale=2.0: 0.28s -> 0 found"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3256,"aggregated":"Upperbody scale=0.8: 1.14s -> 0 found\nUpperbody scale=1.0: 0.83s -> 1 found\nUpperbody scale=1.5: 0.39s -> 1 found\nUpperbody scale=2.0: 0.28s -> 0 found","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796096309}}
{"type":"message","id":"a90ad51d","parentId":"d505f93c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:28:29.647Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cascade detection is slow: 1-2 seconds per scale. But we can see that at scale=1.0 and 1.5 we get 1 detection each.\n\nLet me use a smarter approach:\n1. Only use scale=1.0 and 1.5 (2 scales instead of 4) - saves 2s\n2. Only use upperbody cascade (saves another ~1s)\n\nThis gives us about 0.8+0.4 = 1.2s per frame. Still not real-time but better.\n\nActually, for uploaded videos (not real-time), 1-2 seconds per frame is fine. The issue is more about the queue filling up if we have a video with many frames to process.\n \nFor uploaded videos, I can pre-buffer frames while processing, but for real-time webcam at 2 FPS, 1.2s per frame means the processing loop lags behind the camera. The user's actual complaint is that the uploaded video is lagging and hasn't finished processing yet, which suggests the 4K video is either taking too long or getting stuck in the queue.\n\nWith 2 FPS target and each frame taking 1.78s to process, the detection loop falls behind almost immediately. I need to either reduce the detection resolution to 720p to cut processing time in half, or use the existing MOG2-based approach for the demo video while switching to Haar cascades only for uploaded content where people are stationary.\n\nActually, a hybrid approach makes more sense: use Haar cascades as the primary detector since it works on stationary subjects, keep the processing resolution at 720p to stay fast enough for real-time performance, and strip out the MOG2 logic entirely.","thinkingSignature":"2f2f98815d9ae13972e3c5b204742df3e211428fcd24ed5fba315ed10962765d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5cn0yecjbvua_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 960    # Max width for detection (speed vs accuracy)","newText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 720    # Max width for fast detection (Haar cascade is slow)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":119,"output":457,"cacheRead":138898,"cacheWrite":587,"totalTokens":140061,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796096374,"responseId":"0636f4c20ebcce5054e5203292ce5ba8"}}
