{"type":"message","id":"5566eb3c","parentId":"d22416ac","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:29:10.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good! 2 seconds per frame at 1280p for the uploaded video, and 0.93s for the demo video. \n\nFor the demo video at 720p, 0.93s per frame. With FPS_TARGET=2, we have 500ms per frame. So the processing will lag. But for uploaded video, the lag is less of an issue since it's not real-time.\n\nActually, the issue is that the backend can't keep up with the video processing rate. The user uploaded a 4K video and the processing is too slow. Let me think about this differently:\n\nFor **uploaded videos** (not real-time):\n\n\n- Speed doesn't matter much — the user just wants to see the analysis results\n- The issue is that it takes too long (minutes) to process the whole video\n- I should prioritize accuracy and accept slower processing\n\nFor **real-time webcam**:\n- Speed matters — needs to process faster than the frame rate\n- FPS_TARGET=2 means 500ms per frame\n- Current speed: 0.93s per frame (720p) = TOO SLOW\n\nFor the uploaded video, the problem is the video has 391 frames and we're processing at 2 FPS, so it would take about 3 minutes to get through the whole thing. That's why the user sees \"đang phân tích\" and nothing happening — the first frame takes 2 seconds to process and then nothing displays until it finishes. I should check what FPS the demo video is actually running at.","thinkingSignature":"d5822e238d269c07fc3d8ee9ec6b8519d14bed79b994b0a8202a7decce699f58"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wn99zpvp0d4p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2\nfor f, label in [\n    ('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4', 'demo'),\n    ('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4', '4K upload')\n]:\n    cap = cv2.VideoCapture(f)\n    fps = cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS)\n    frames = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_COUNT))\n    w = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))\n    h = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))\n    cap.release()\n    print(f'{label}: {w}x{h} @ {fps:.1f}fps, {frames} frames, duration: {frames/fps:.1f}s')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":136,"output":553,"cacheRead":140067,"cacheWrite":1193,"totalTokens":141949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796137566,"responseId":"0636f4ebbb04a177fdca3ae8235d0af7"}}
