{"type":"message","id":"8bbbf945","parentId":"9a762117","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:29:20.654Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n- Demo video: 15 FPS, 225 frames, 15 seconds. At 2 FPS processing, 225/2 = 112.5 seconds ≈ 2 minutes to process everything. That's fine for uploaded video.\n- 4K upload: 24 FPS, 391 frames, 16.3 seconds. At 2 FPS processing, 391/2 = 195.5 seconds ≈ 3.3 minutes.\n\nFor uploaded videos, this is acceptable — the user uploads and waits a few minutes. The issue is that the user sees the analysis hasn't started yet because the first frame takes 2s to process.","thinkingSignature":"a5b6a7bbb16512b4efdfaafb893b53abe5776b7cb9af4cd3da7e892c55923187"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s8chn4zs5145_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181225_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4')\nfps = cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FPS)\nframes = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_COUNT))\nw = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_WIDTH))\nh = int(cap.get(cv2.CAP_PROP_FRAME_HEIGHT))\ncap.release()\nprint(f'Upload 1: {w}x{h} @ {fps:.1f}fps, {frames} frames')\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":102,"output":312,"cacheRead":140718,"cacheWrite":1199,"totalTokens":142331,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796151507,"responseId":"0636f4f901d34903d7f57212ac5f4e5d"}}
