{"type":"message","id":"46aae9dd","parentId":"94a4b99f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:29:33.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both uploaded videos are 4K @ 24fps, 391 frames (~16 seconds). At 2 FPS processing with 2s per frame, it would take 391/2 = 195 seconds ≈ 3.25 minutes to process the full video. This is long but acceptable for an uploaded video.\n\nThe real issue is that the backend processing starts from frame 0 and takes 2s per frame. The user uploads and sees nothing for the first 2 seconds, then maybe a few frames processed, then nothing for a while.\n\nFor the demo video (720p @ 15fps), the demo video processes at ~1s per frame. At 2 FPS target, this is borderline — the processing time (1s) is close to the target interval (0.5s). The queue will grow slowly.\n \nThe bottleneck seems to be that the user is waiting for the analysis to complete and display. With 391 frames taking roughly 3 minutes at 2 FPS, that's a long wait, and I suspect the demo video processing is also running in the background simultaneously, which could be hogging resources. I'm going to increase the FPS target for uploaded videos to 5 and reduce the resolution to 720p to speed up processing significantly.","thinkingSignature":"082a633915f80e1c88d340dbaca5b6f6cff6916edb91afde534c630d61fbe189"},{"type":"text","text":"4K video @ 24fps = 391 frames, 3+ phút để process hết. Tăng tốc bằng cách:\n1. Downscale 4K → 720p (nhanh hơn ~4x)\n2. Tăng FPS target cho upload\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ziadypok0u3w_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 720    # Max width for fast detection (Haar cascade is slow)","newText":"    MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 720    # Max width for fast Haar cascade detection"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":68,"output":428,"cacheRead":141359