{"type":"message","id":"8ddc3237","parentId":"46aae9dd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:29:33.260Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ziadypok0u3w_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  16     Designed for real-time streaming mode.\n  17     Auto-downscales 4K video to 720p for CPU performance.\n  18     \"\"\"\n  19 \n- 20     MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 720    # Max width for fast detection (Haar cascade is slow)\n+ 20     MAX_PROC_WIDTH = 720    # Max width for fast Haar cascade detection\n  21 \n  22     def __init__(self, video_path: str = None, use_webcam: bool = False, fps_target: int = 5):\n  23         self.video_path = video_path\n  24         self.use_webcam = use_webcam\n     ...","firstChangedLine":20},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796173222}}
{"type":"message","id":"87452749","parentId":"8ddc3237","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:29:48.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also, I should change the FPS_TARGET for the upload to be higher. The default is 2. For 4K uploads, maybe I should set it to 5. But how do I know if the uploaded video is 4K? I can check the resolution in the upload handler.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The issue is that at 2 FPS and 2 seconds per frame, the backend queue fills up faster than it processes. \n\nFor a video with 391 frames at 24fps, the video plays for 16 seconds. The processing at 2 FPS with 2s per frame would take 391 * 0.5s = 195 seconds (3.25 minutes). But the first frame takes 2 seconds, and then subsequent frames are queued.\n\n\nThe real bottleneck is that processing a single frame takes 2 seconds, so with a 2 FPS target, the queue gets ahead of the processor. I could bump the FPS to 5 and downscale uploads to 720p to cut processing time down to around 0.5 seconds per frame, which would let it keep pace with the incoming frames much better.\n\nFor the demo video at 720p, processing is faster at 1 second per frame, so with FPS_TARGET=2 I need to either increase that to 3 or improve the speed. The user's main complaints are the lag on uploaded videos and the lack of results shown, which points to the slow processing speed and missing feedback in the UI while analysis is running.\n\nI should focus on three key improvements: downscaling to 720p for faster processing, bumping the FPS target to 5, and adding a progress indicator to the frontend so users know the analysis is actually happening. Since the upload video is 4K, downscaling to 720p and using a 2 FPS target should let each frame process in about 0.5 seconds, which is much more manageable.","thinkingSignature":"78f12055d36454fd12be7a467d714eb5a9cd9cfbf291d67cf73f9613c6820fa5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9vknvkzgrett_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2, sys, time\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\n# 4K at 720p\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/frontend/public/video/uploaded_20260421_181846_4430419-uhd_3840_2160_24fps.mp4')\nfor i in range(50): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\nproc = cv2.resize(frame, (720, int(frame.shape[0] * 720/frame.shape[1])))\nprint(f'4K at 720p: {proc.shape}')\nstart = time.time()\ndets = det.detect_from_frame(proc)\nprint(f'{time.time()-start:.2f}s, {len(dets)} people')\nfor d in dets:\n    print(f'  [{d[\\\"bbox\\\"][0]:.0f},{d[\\\"bbox\\\"][1]:.0f}] '\n          f'{d[\\\"width\\\"]:.0f}x{d[\\\"height\\\"]:.0f} '\n          f'H={d[\\\"ppe_status\\\"][\\\"has_helmet\\\"]} V={d[\\\"ppe_status\\\"][\\\"has_vest\\\"]}')\n\"","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":75,"output":734,"cacheRead":141982,"cacheWrite":781,"totalTokens":143572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796173281,"responseId":"0636f50f974c7926b1b6e320358131f1"}}
