{"type":"message","id":"62330fcf","parentId":"5681f430","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:30:05.754Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"At 720p (actually 720x405 since it's letterboxed), the detection takes only 0.44 seconds and finds 1 person. But the frame is resized to 720x405 which is a weird aspect ratio (the original 3840x2160 → 720x405 is letterboxed to 720p).\n\nFor the VideoProcessor, I should resize to 720p maintaining aspect ratio, but the issue is that Haar cascades work best at 1:1 or close aspect ratios. Let me resize to 720x720 (square) instead, or just resize to 720x480 (DVD aspect).\n\nActually, the best approach: resize to 720x480 (DVD resolution, standard for OpenCV cascades).","thinkingSignature":"3241f36157b3550809759806921af5b0a1789a19ebfc46bcfb7a8bb33727a675"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tv16ajafrjgz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"            # ── Auto-downscale 4K/1080p for faster CPU processing ──────────\n                orig_h, orig_w = frame.shape[:2]\n                if orig_w > self.MAX_PROC_WIDTH:\n                    scale = self.MAX_PROC_WIDTH / orig_w\n                    proc_w = self.MAX_PROC_WIDTH\n                    proc_h = int(orig_h * scale)\n                    proc_frame = cv2.resize(frame, (proc_w, proc_h))\n                    self._proc_scale = scale\n                else:\n                    proc_frame = frame\n                    self._proc_scale = 1.0","newText":"            # ── Auto-downscale for faster CPU Haar cascade processing ────────\n                orig_h, orig_w = frame.shape[:2]\n                # Target: 720x480 (DVD resolution, fast for OpenCV)\n                target_w, target_h = 720, 480\n                scale = min(target_w / orig_w, target_h / orig_h)\n                proc_w, proc_h = int(orig_w * scale), int(orig_h * scale)\n                # Ensure even dimensions (required by OpenCV)\n                proc_w, proc_h = proc_w // 2 * 2, proc_h // 2 * 2\n                proc_frame = cv2.resize(frame, (proc_w, proc_h))\n                self._proc_scale = orig_w / proc_w  # scale for bbox coordinates"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":87,"output":513,"cacheRead":142330,"cacheWrite":1210,"totalTokens":144140,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796194535,"responseId":"0636f524f8cf04450f451482d3e93ec1"}}
