{"type":"message","id":"4305163e","parentId":"dca497fa","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:30:41.132Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:- Demo video (720x1280): 0.84s per frame, 2 people detected\n- 4K upload (downscaled to 720x480): 0.48s per frame, 1 person detectedWith FPS_TARGET=2:- Demo: 0.84s/frame > 0.5s interval → processing is slightly behind real-time, but queue will grow slowly- 4K: 0.48s/frame < 0.5s interval → can almost keep up\n\nThe issue is that the processing for the demo video at 1280x720 takes 0.84s. The MAX_PROC_WIDTH is now 720, so for the demo video (1280x720), it would resize to 720x720. Let me test that.","thinkingSignature":"36db115a4703a0d3da5aac5653b4b4847acf022e5307f234255518da13fd07de"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yxyfwzk49wuh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport cv2, sys, time\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\n# Demo at 720x720 (new target)\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\nfor i in range(30): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\nproc = cv2.resize(frame, (720, int(frame.shape[0] * 720/frame.shape[1])))\nproc = cv2.resize(proc, (720, 480))\nprint(f'Demo at 720x480: {proc.shape}')\nstart = time.time()\ndets = det.detect_from_frame(proc)\nprint(f'{time.time()-start:.2f}s, {len(dets)} people')\nfor d in dets:\n    print(f'  [{d[\\\"bbox\\\"][0]:.0f},{d[\\\"bbox\\\"][1]:.0f}] '\n          f'{d[\\\"width\\\"]:.0f}x{d[\\\"height\\\"]:.0f} '\n          f'H={d[\\\"ppe_status\\\"][\\\"has_helmet\\\"]} V={d[\\\"ppe_status\\\"][\\\"has_vest\\\"]}')\n\"","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":98,"output":496,"cacheRead":144146,"cacheWrite":777,"totalTokens":145517,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"to