{"type":"message","id":"fc9531cb","parentId":"1da8bd52","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:31:29.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"238 frames processed but 0 detections. Something is wrong. Let me check if the detector is working correctly. The VideoProcessor uses the new detector (Haar cascade) but the `_get_foreground` method is no longer in the new detector. Let me check what `process_single_frame` does in the detector.\n\nActually, looking at the new detector, the `process_frame` method calls `detect_from_frame`. The `detect_from_frame` uses Haar cascades, NOT `_get_foreground`. But the VideoProcessor calls `process_single_frame`, which for the VideoProcessor is defined differently from the detector's `process_frame`.","thinkingSignature":"1487c36aa66a9f9520f1e1a1626000e7c271f7163adf4ee84e3330449dc21ffa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bprz8ugevtzs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"def process_single_frame\\|detector.process_frame\\|detector.detect\" \\\n  /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":69,"output":205,"cacheRead":146166,"cacheWrite":578,"totalTokens":147018,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796281798,"responseId":"0636f57b5fdf882692f2d5ee59f1a2ec"}}
