{"type":"message","id":"b8f9f154","parentId":"7fdd8373","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:31:35.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good - `process_single_frame` calls `self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)`. And the new detector uses Haar cascades. Let me check what `rgb_frame` is in `process_single_frame`:","thinkingSignature":"88d80de93206b9dbcd0fe37751133cb2b72edd8785c6861e0604a4bc2ff3f071"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fclpvkdgmco5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","offset":86,"limit":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":74,"output":109,"cacheRead":146428,"cacheWrite":558,"totalTokens":147169,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796289586,"responseId":"0636f583c9dcd56b3f451a808d63412e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"651d323b","parentId":"b8f9f154","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:31:35.571Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fclpvkdgmco5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    def process_single_frame(self, frame):\n        \"\"\"\n        Process a single frame directly (for API use).\n        Returns (annotated_frame, detections, summary)\n        \"\"\"\n        rgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n        detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)\n        summary = self.detector.get_summary(detections)\n        violations = self.detector.get_violations(detections)\n\n\n[132 more lines in file. Use offset=96 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796295556}}
{"type":"message","id":"4823bc28","parentId":"651d323b","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:31:53.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - `process_single_frame` calls `self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)`. The `rgb_frame` is a BGR→RGB converted version of the `frame`. The detector's `detect_from_frame` expects a BGR frame (since it calls `cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)`). Wait, let me check:\n\nIn the new detector:\n```python\ndef detect_from_frame(self, frame: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]:\n    ...\n    gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n\n\n```\n\nSo it expects BGR. But the VideoProcessor passes RGB. This could be causing the issue! Let me check if this is the problem.\n\nActually, in OpenCV, `cv2.cvtColor` with `COLOR_BGR2GRAY` uses the formula `0.299*R + 0.587*G + 0.114*B`. If the input is actually RGB (not BGR), then the conversion would be wrong, but it wouldn't crash - it would just produce incorrect grayscale values. The cascade detection might still work with slightly wrong grayscale values, but it would be less accurate. The real issue is likely that the cascade detector isn't finding anything because the grayscale conversion is off, which would explain why `all_boxes` ends up empty.\n\nLet me check what the VideoProcessor is actually passing to the detector. Looking at `_process_loop`, it's resizing the frame to 720x480 and then converting from BGR to RGB before passing to `process_single_frame`, which then passes it to `detect_from_frame`. So there's a BGR→RGB conversion happening somewhere that's making the cascade work with the wrong color space.\n\n```\n\npython\nrgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n```\n\nWait, that's also converting to grayscale, which doesn't make sense if we're using color-based detection. Let me trace through this more carefully to see what the detector is actually receiving.\n\nAh, I see it now - `process_single_frame` converts the frame to RGB, but then `detect_from_frame` tries to convert it as if it's BGR. That's definitely a mismatch in the color space handling. The fix would be to either pass the frame as-is to the detector without the extra conversion, or convert it to BGR before calling `detect_from_frame`.\n\nActually, I think the real problem is that the demo video was working fine before because it used motion-based detection, but now the Haar cascade approach is fundamentally different. Let me test the detector directly on the demo video frame at the correct resolution to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"aadb99643122dabfd81996a16e139ea60059bc038e8fe6930997309c28a732a2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wegzvkvcv12l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport cv2, sys, time\nsys.path.insert(0, '/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend')\nfrom detector import PPEDetector\n\ndet = PPEDetector()\n\n# Test demo video\ncap = cv2.VideoCapture('/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/demo.mp4')\nfor i in range(30): cap.read()\nret, frame = cap.read()\ncap.release()\n\n# Process like VideoProcessor does (resize to 720x480)\nproc = cv2.resize(frame, (720, int(frame.shape[0] * 720/frame.shape[1])))\nproc = cv2.resize(proc, (720, 480))\nprint(f\"Proc shape: {proc.shape}\")\n\n# Try BGR vs RGB\nprint(\"\\nBGR (correct):\")\ndets_bgr = det.detect_from_frame(proc)\nprint(f\"  {len(dets_bgr)} people\")\nfor d in dets_bgr:\n    print(f\"  [{d['bbox'][0]:.0f},{d['bbox'][1]:.0f}] {d['width']:.0f}x{d['height']:.0f} H={d['ppe_status']['has_helmet']} V={d['ppe_status']['has_vest']}\")\n\nprint(\"\\nRGB (wrong):\")\nrgb = cv2.cvtColor(proc, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\ndets_rgb = det.detect_from_frame(rgb)\nprint(f\"  {len(dets_rgb)} people\")\nPYEOF","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":156,"output":923,"cacheRead":146776,"cacheWrite":361,"totalTokens":148216,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796295585,"responseId":"0636f58922d007b7f535a17cfa4f876f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f69879d4","parentId":"4823bc28","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:31:54.233Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wegzvkvcv12l_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Proc shape: (480, 720, 3)\n\nBGR (correct):\n  3 people\n  [292,302] 100x81 H=True V=False\n  [58,309] 92x75 H=True V=False\n  [202,238] 35x71 H=True V=False\n\nRGB (wrong):\n  0 people"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1060,"aggregated":"Proc shape: (480, 720, 3)\n\nBGR (correct):\n  3 people\n  [292,302] 100x81 H=True V=False\n  [58,309] 92x75 H=True V=False\n  [202,238] 35x71 H=True V=False\n\nRGB (wrong):\n  0 people","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776796314217}}
{"type":"message","id":"1072caea","parentId":"f69879d4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:32:10.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The VideoProcessor passes RGB to `detect_from_frame`, but the detector expects BGR. That's why 0 detections! The VideoProcessor does:\n```python\nrgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)\n```But the detector does:```python\ngray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)```\n\nSo when RGB is passed, it treats it as BGR and converts to grayscale using the wrong formula, resulting in garbage grayscale values and 0 cascade detections.\n\nThe fix: in `process_single_frame`, don't convert to RGB, just pass the BGR frame directly to the detector.","thinkingSignature":"64d8aa4c99de6d6a3719692dbc0d19e7e5b5c71c4099593fd8338140c013dae8"},{"type":"text","text":"Tìm ra bug! VideoProcessor convert BGR→RGB rồi detector lại convert BGR→GRAY — nhầm màu. Fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t27p4ei828n1_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/projects/s1-ppe-safety/backend/video_processor.py","edits":[{"oldText":"    def process_single_frame(self, frame):\n        \"\"\"\n        Process a single frame directly (for API use).\n        Returns (annotated_frame, detections, summary)\n        \"\"\"\n        rgb_frame = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(rgb_frame)","newText":"    def process_single_frame(self, frame):\n        \"\"\"\n        Process a single frame directly (for API use).\n        Returns (annotated_frame, detections, summary)\n        \"\"\"\n        # Pass BGR frame directly to detector\n        detections = self.detector.detect_from_frame(frame)"}]}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":123,"output":400,"cacheRead":147023,"cacheWrite":1161,"totalTokens":148707,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776796314246,"responseId":"0636f5a1b182a7c63df26b043e1c4016"}}
