{"type":"message","id":"deda63f8","parentId":"acebd4d4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:48:46.445Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user chose option 1: **Nâng cao độ chính xác detection**. They want to improve the detection accuracy, likely by integrating a YOLO model or better algorithm.\n\nLet me plan this carefully. We need:\n1. A better detection model - YOLO (ONNX) or MediaPipe\n2. Still CPU-only since we're on a VPS without GPU\n\nOptions for better detection:\n1. **YOLOv8 via ONNX Runtime** - Lightweight, CPU-friendly\n2. **MediaPipe** - Google's solution, very fast on CPU\n3. **SSD MobileNet** - TensorFlow Lite, fast\n\n\n4. **Fine-tuned YOLO** - Too heavy for this environment\n\nI'm leaning toward ONNX Runtime with a pre-trained person detection model since it's fast on CPU, though I need to verify the available packages and disk space. The download itself shouldn't be an issue given the minimal file sizes involved.\n\nThe real constraint is figuring out whether to use Ultralytics directly or the ONNX Runtime approach, since installing ultralytics pulls in CUDA dependencies that won't work on CPU. I should check what's actually available and viable within the disk budget. Installing YOLOv8 via pip would require CUDA dependencies we don't have, so instead I should download the ONNX model file directly and use ONNX Runtime to run it—it's lighter and CPU-compatible. Let me verify we have enough disk space, then fetch the YOLOv8n ONNX model from the official repository. Writing ONNX detection code...","thinkingSignature":"b16dff4c505b14e716e964910f292036c8abaced7b37e3a9a23c033e0b934ad5"},{"type":"text","text":"\nƯu tiên 1 — Nâng cao detection. Bắt đầu với **YOLOv8n ONNX model** (nhẹ, chạy được trên CPU):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jhttyqdmh7ir_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"df -h / | tail -1\necho \"---\"\npip3 show onnxruntime 2>/dev/null | head -2 || echo \"onnxruntime not installed\"\npip3 show ultralytics 2>/dev/null | head -2 || echo \"ultralytics not installed\"\npython3 -c \"import onnxruntime; print('ONNX Runtime:', onnxruntime.__version__)\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"ONNX Runtime not available\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":491,"cacheRead":158859,"cacheWrite":1195,"totalTokens":160545,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776797311728,"responseId":"0636f9819cba2152825f1c631d44baec"}}
