{"type":"message","id":"a51ef9f8","parentId":"39d2e461","timestamp":"2026-04-21T18:48:58.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Disk is at 99% (only 420MB free). ONNX Runtime not installed. Let me try installing it, and also check if we can use MediaPipe or the ONNX model.Actually, let me think about this more carefully. With only 420MB free, installing ONNX Runtime (which is ~50MB with its dependencies) should be fine. But we also need to download the YOLO model (~6MB for YOLOv8n).\n\nLet me try:\n1. Install onnxruntime (pip install onnxruntime)\n2. Download YOLOv8n ONNX model\n3. Write the detection code\n\n\n4. But wait—the previous attempts to install ultralytics filled the disk because of all the CUDA and PyTorch dependencies. onnxruntime is much simpler with no GPU requirements, so it shouldn't have the same problem.\n\nLet me go ahead and install onnxruntime and see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"d605ab24a410868fe36dbbff9453839bf7769289df74b590ad79fa2285d805ab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b4rwteetp2oz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip3 install onnxruntime --quiet 2>&1 | tail -3","yieldMs":55000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":75,"output":252,"cacheRead":159749,"cacheWrite":764,"totalTokens":160840,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776797329343,"responseId":"0636f99362e277d797ec0191065365f4"}}
